title: The Boathouse Restaurant
address: 2770 Esplanade Ave, Port Moody, BC V3H 0C8
descriptions: Waterfront option for local, sustainable seafood & premium steaks, plus wines from British Columbia.

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Eunice Zhao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_m19zpDnShMlACSrl6S-cDalRdCNjiwxQ6t6OmcK7Ajk5cQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This restaurant offers a lovely waterfront view, creating a pleasant atmosphere for dining. The ingredients are fresh, and the service is attentive. The seafood chowder was rich and flavorful, brimming with fresh seafood that complemented the creamy base perfectly. The grilled ahi tuna was cooked to perfection, with a nice sear on the outside while remaining tender and juicy inside. However, the menu selection is quite limited, which may not satisfy those seeking variety. The prices are more in line with fine dining, though the food and service quality feel average for the cost. On the plus side, we only had to wait about 10 minutes for a table around 2pm","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODw1yHuYOaYmXeVpNvsTlV7FFk0RB7MvUz8yE&fid=0x0:0x5aa213bcccc48530"],"When":"2024-12-25"},{"Name":"Rolando_ Rose","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIQBfjayv2V3eqQ6nmwU1uOEqgsWCG5VdwRxO3uXCF1EsXQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Ambiance of the restaurant is stylish with pacific northwest design. Tables are lovely with white linens, restaurant is spacious with patio seating as well. Nice views of water, mountains and the Rocky Point Park. Food was average in terms of presentation and flavour profile. Calamari was too thinly sliced with overly sweet sauce, acidity was somewhat lacking. Wedge Caesar salad was not appealing, insufficient dressing. Mixed grill seafood with zucchini and carrots: you can elevate this dish by using asparagus and baby carrots instead, and with a few microgreens garnish. Trust me, it’ll make a difference! We concluded our meal with coffee and dessert. Molten chocolate lava cake could’ve been better if there’s a garnish, just a piece of raspberry or blackberry or half strawberry, that would really make a big difference! After our lunch, we strolled at the Rocky Point Park which is just a steps away from the restaurant. Nice park with beautiful views, boardwalk, boat launch and boat rentals to name a few; with plenty of amenities for young and young at heart!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvLXyTzdfnjl-68UsR-08GHFXy7UjA-OxCGcs&fid=0x0:0x5aa213bcccc48530"],"When":"2024-10-25"},{"Name":"Jeremiah Hunter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVstOeDb0cNM2liNN27VZdumnDhp7SGpgbz_3sZFvnpsJHHzKw6Pg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Overall, positive experience with the atmosphere. Restaurant furnishings etc are nice. Waiters were good. Ordered the halibut fish and chips. I would have been impressed with the food if it was half the price. I figure that you're paying for the view, which was quite nice. And I've had worse experiences at places where I'm paying for the view. Ordered the Perfect Storm cocktail. Not recommended but was the other cocktails all looked very interesting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO33TAVlaerPIYemOtM-cvQ6vUT3N0nsTZQxfQV&fid=0x0:0x5aa213bcccc48530"],"When":"2024-8-8"},{"Name":"Emily","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVnUYp6B39XV6d8C5kgeglVvQzUj0_MZRgXvwAElCXqqRYybMdL=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"It was a very disappointing dinning experience with poor food quality at a high cost.

The atmosphere there was awesome and all of us were excited at the beginning. We sat at the patio, the server kept chasing us for ordering food. She came to chase us at least 3 times in about 5mins. No patience at all.

We have spent about $190 in total. The food portion was very small, especially the seafood tower and steak. The lobster tail was spongy, no taste, not fresh at all. Oyster and mussel were tiny. What’s worst was, all food came to the table almost at the same time. The table was full and we couldn’t enjoy the food one by one. The food was cold, not enjoyable at all.

It was a birthday celebration. I remarked it when I made the reservation online and reconfirmed again with a phone call. It was expecting to have a complementary desert to surprise my loved one but turned out nothing at the end. It made me very disappointed and upset. I totally regretted to choose this restaurant.

After the dinner, I went to the disabled washroom with my little kids for more space. It was totally disgusting. The floor was wet, hand towel paper and toilet paper were on the floor. It was even worst than a public washroom at the park.

I was not willing to pay the tips at all but still paid a bit. I cried out after the dinner and tried to find out the email address to express my feelings after the dinner. I then found out the cost of the kids meal should be $0.99 during Sep 2-30. Why the server still charged me the regular price?? It was kind of cheating.

Totally not recommend to anyone.

————-

I have already sent email to the restaurant on Sep 2 but nobody follow up.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN1V2FVfLLXo-n6x-sL5vigxsoYa-5GcikyCY94&fid=0x0:0x5aa213bcccc48530"],"When":"2024-9-4"},{"Name":"J Q","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWWLFaR2htiLNLIQAXB2-FbuNystyoB794RiAm0Uo82lJgg8OdK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Everything we tried was very enjoyable, and the fries were especially delicious. Our server was attentive and friendly, enhancing our experience. Sitting on the patio offers a wonderful lake view, making the meal even more memorable. Overall, a great dining experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzU5DRUh7UjMGsT8UCypHy-3Hokw2gjziQP33Q&fid=0x0:0x5aa213bcccc48530"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Cortney Reine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJXEho0FdodYSCZpvRgaE-SfKuTQk3gaNebJTu6PShWDa0Lcw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Such a gorgeous spot on the water.     I asked for a surprise, since everything looked good.    The halibut was the best I've ever, ever, EVER tasted.     The oysters were incredible.     What a great experience!

One thing I thought was funny was the oxymoron sign out front; '$3 complementary parking'

Gave us a chuckle :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfUInqh_blXYutlZAzIjM93JBQy65eZi_U-2d-&fid=0x0:0x5aa213bcccc48530"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"Maggie Liu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0JYUBsNfHmstgM8KPbHPNmE5htG-ybajcuzCE_0lTSNNY0R1L=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I used to come to Boathouse every now and then a few years ago, and this was my first trip back in a while.
The restaurant is better than ever.
Firstly, it’s probably amongst the prettiest restaurants around.
The oysters are fresh and cleaned well. The bread is great.
There is a wide array of share items and entrees available all day.
The servers are polite and attentive.
Highly recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMaHEbbfHKWXX9P3yGwhqMq2U1OB-TogZ7Ytl8I&fid=0x0:0x5aa213bcccc48530"],"When":"2024-9-7"},{"Name":"Elham Shahbandy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8v0FqiWfwrKZlKpvymmkhzMYhJ-PBGxv_Ot_SbQhp9uNsQ3Yb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Price was reasonable but not really tasty. Shiitake fried rice was not really eatable. Steak was good but Cesar salad had a strong cheese smell and taste which was not pleasant to eat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPd8LR5ObgHfzi-Ni6BV7AEE_V4apVi64RrMoo2&fid=0x0:0x5aa213bcccc48530"],"When":"2024-8-9"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Pradyumna Gujjar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVHYwZPoeWTWb_r-Pj3URXZmwvjMuE8IJLkPSR4xqAVv86CR0HjQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"One of the better brunch places here in port moody and the neighboring areas.
The food tastes great, good atmosphere and service is fast.
We their the baileys flight, which in my opinion, could be improved. We couldn’t really make out the difference between the different flavors except for the peanut butter one.
The Maui Thai chicken burger was awesome and we was the Yorkshire Benny. I also loved their take on the hash browns.
They could definitely work on the pricing as we found it a bit on the expensive side.
Would def recommend this spot for anyone looking for a good brunch spot!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPToGwTm2g2cjL5bBjFYtzUui484e0jSqqK2tE&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Aaron Brousseau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrpCaHqR-XwUoFEei3pehP3F8y3p8zpxIo1yJXL2DI8WHkRvkE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had an amazing brunch at The Hard Bean Brunch Co. in Port Moody! The food was absolutely phenomenal—every bite was bursting with flavor. The vibe of the place was spot on, cozy yet lively, and the beverage selection was outstanding. Whether you're into coffee, juices, or something a bit stronger, they've got you covered. Our server, Josh, was fantastic—attentive, friendly, and made the experience even better. If you're looking for a brunch spot that nails it on all fronts, this is the place! 10 out of 10 hits all key points for a brunch spots.  Ps the patio was Lovely And is dog friendly which is a huge plus for me.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMNaHI05Lx6EisqaeHHwsYPAftWP6Jdr06aQfbG&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Parneet Kahlon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqz_l5BzN5_mBY3QC7SEZWEVervEPkE_VocF-ECzkBQsGcdPO6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a nice brunch place in Port Moody.

The place had ample seating and since we had our puppy with us and patio seating was perfect for us.

Food we ordered was very delicious and prepared in a timely manner.

For drinks we ordered coke and mimosa. Mimosa was good but we were expecting a nice tall glass.

Maui teriyaki chicken burger - it was very juicy and delicious…. 10/10 for the flavour

Hard Chicken crunch - Again flavours 10/10 chicken was cooked perfectly

Last but not the least, Hard bean co burger, very nice vegetarian options. Bean patty was very nice not too dry..

Definitely hoping to visit soon, been looking at so many more options to try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1KrvVRsRO_zbgmwGyZyuW9bPr71yR3bhKnNq5&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-7-31"},{"Name":"Billy Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVSxOBk_c92Ol0FCdQI2uK9UOXNvJt85D76p4UHFqKR_gkp-zYHgw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve been to a lot of brunch places this year and I’ve always been underwhelmed by the concept of brunch. Well, The Hard Bean Brunch Co. broke the mold.

First off, amazing service, people were so friendly and helpful. $6 all day specials as well for drinks.

Ordered the Yorkshire pudding hard ham Benny. Out of this world. Probably will never order a Benny elsewhere ever again. The smashed potatoes were out of this world. Crispy on the outside soft on the inside. Wife ordered the quesadilla and that was equally amazing. One small knock was that ham waffle fries were a bit undercooked but don’t get that anyways, stick with the smashed potatoes!!

We will be back if we’re ever in the neighborhood.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7JAnb6jeZFhYaQ6sJ8zdxRiRMdkaulczFv38U&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"Mandy Sam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfdcmtmnw1QBUKzc568p_XlShrjauBmzaYnb3AklL4JCX7IFSL3g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"On Sunday, I visited the restaurant with a group of four for a late lunch. Upon our arrival, we were informed that the wait time would be approximately 25 to 30 minutes, which we were happy to accommodate. While waiting, we took a leisurely stroll around the area. After 26 minutes, we received a notification that our table was ready, and we were promptly seated.

The restaurant's interior displayed a lively and welcoming ambiance, creating a wonderful atmosphere and vibe. Our server provided attentive service, checking in on us periodically. However, there were instances when we wanted to place additional orders but had to wait for a while before our server returned. We ordered a diverse selection of dishes, including the rose spaghettini, Julius salad, everything grilled cheese, hard bean co burger, and hard chicken crunch. The handheld dishes were pretty good. The hard chicken crunch lived up to its name, delivering an exceptionally crispy texture. The Julius salad was enjoyable, although the dressing could have benefited from a touch more acidity. Regrettably, the rose spaghettini seemed to lack in terms of flavor.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2M-uiySMHfptiI6rZzA40nKLqNvQnsjzaLR6d&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Zain Bhanji","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKlgk8aN8btcOJZzZf5wvoL31ZimhDnrY-IWz_-xujZJutZcBjZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was an upbeat and lively brunch spot! Great music, cool set up and loved the colour scheme of the place. Service was quick and friendly here, however the serving sizes are quite small and not filling enough. I ordered the steak tacos and although I even ordered a side of fruit at the recommendation of the server, it still wasn’t enough to fill me up. I felt the resto could have been more generous with adding more meat to each of my tacos. Regardless, these tacos were quite small - pretty much a 2 bite eat, which in my opinion isn’t worth the $18 you pay for the plate.
Would consider coming back here but having something else hopefully more filling!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNShnQT9frNbDmQjQgCIY3Hm7YQJsMWry9askrq&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"Golnaz J N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwh094AvMjRiNSQoo9HjnFTPUMh8c3XSGOFZ78okUlI4KLdqnN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I tried the yam waffle fries and Bacon Burger with a delicious Green Salad, and it was an exceptional dining experience. The burger, perfectly cooked and topped with crispy bacon, was juicy and flavorful, offering a delightful blend of savory and smoky tastes. I asked for lettuce wrap for the burger. The yam waffle fries were a standout, crispy on the outside and tender on the inside, with a natural sweetness that complemented the burger perfectly. Accompanying the meal was a fresh and vibrant green salad, featuring a mix of crisp lettuce, juicy tomatoes, crumble feta cheese and quinoas. This combination made for a well-rounded and satisfying meal, balancing indulgence with a touch of freshness. Highly recommended for anyone seeking a delicious and hearty bite!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOUaR5a8FLR6B3otK7luPOQG3JxexiCAA5PCQA&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-7-15"},{"Name":"Mounota","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvpiSPg9AtpTNs-8JJvoJHojdmAI1FZcME9pprQbBKumVFhadS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The atmosphere was pleasant. I had their smoothie bowl. It was okay; tasted a little watery. It looked pretty though. I might return and try their other dishes because the reviews are so positive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMW-NUkGkpjmqUH4iPJ4DTyhMBN9ZyBBys53Ycn&fid=0x0:0x4acbc2a73f7224be"],"When":"2024-11-21"}]

[{"Name":"R J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFsVCoG7z_n2p2NuKtYVduptbixBrj7EdY_3gYWBr1b3AgPslD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We only discovered Float 30 recently and quickly became regulars!
The restaurant is a gem and is the best kept secret between Port Moody and Burnaby, tucked away behind Barnet Hwy at the Reed Point Marina.
They have an expansive menu for every palette. It sure beats going to the White Spot! The food is always consistent in flavoring and of generous  portions. The restaurant has 2 cozy patios, pet friendly, one enclosed with heat lamps. Prices are very reasonable. And should you be so fortunate on weekends to have Adrian attend to you. His friendly, warm, genuine personality and outstanding service make for a memorable dining experience without breaking the bank!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0ADu0HMe-ZUxoFqxdUN7mMFqgigEdVCMBpy4&fid=0x0:0x3b98d3acd65c808c"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"K’s coffee lover","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW-385uQOflrqOxsV0QWsdIyhv-rxdZ7rLwLnLPmzpfPGzr9P6Z=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I visited on a Thursday evening to try the seafood specials, which are only available from Thursday to Sunday nights. The Fanny Bay Fresh Oysters were the daily special—creamy and incredibly fresh. The Ling Cod Fish and Chips were beautifully presented, with a perfectly coated, buttery crust, fresh and tasty fries, and a well-dressed coleslaw. The signature seafood chowder was rich and packed with seafood flavor.

The seafood boil was abundant with fresh seafood, and while the flavor was mild, a dash of salt or Tabasco balanced it nicely. Though listed as an entree, the portion size was great for sharing.

Our server was friendly and attentive, adding to the experience. We sat outside on a cool evening, comfortably warmed by a heating lamp beside our table, and noticed that other guests were offered blankets upon request. Looking forward to returning on a summer evening to enjoy the view and sunset.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWfOKK7NUBx1VlczsoATov8J8fbWi_KOqWv0yi&fid=0x0:0x3b98d3acd65c808c"],"When":"2024-10-28"},{"Name":"Y. Cherski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-7SLlKKRW0Rqcp9wRXFlvt6gbh0rtI7PMIroLgxETtGiPwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cutting to the chase, this place easily landed in my top 3 favorite spots in the Tri-City area. The atmosphere and cuisine leave little to be desired. Located in the marina, it’s perfect for casual dining or special occasions. Just make sure to plan ahead because snagging a table can be tricky. Don't forget to ask for a free parking ticket when you arrive. The menu is packed with seafood, and the bar’s equally impressive with plenty of great options. We sampled several pasta dishes, and all were exceptional. Oysters are very reasonably priced, which is always a nice bonus. While we didn’t try the fish and chips, seeing how other diners raved about it, I’m definitely ordering some next time. There’s plenty more to love, but I’ll keep it simple—go try it for yourself!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmAJRw6mqxUfmU0CR9sv5MX_j4jMiRIc067IwZ&fid=0x0:0x3b98d3acd65c808c"],"When":"2024-9-20"},{"Name":"Vernessa Lin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW_HMcx5wd1O28ySlJt9n4oU_hrqSI6Z05JLm6P-8L--a68NBo5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"hidden gem off the highway! small cute atmosphere with friendly waitresses. the food comes pretty quickly and has excellent value for the price. 30 dollars for a white wine linguine but it is topped with a good amount of mussels and prawns and there are two slices of bread that come with it! the homemade fries are very good, and the classic chowder has plenty of flavor.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMqqyISDbg60YlZ_Gt8Tt9RF-yUaTd4R7DsY1ix&fid=0x0:0x3b98d3acd65c808c"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's a small gem of a restaurant tucked away from the highway. There are lots of good parking but make sure to get the parking slip from one of the employees at the restaurant.

The service and the food were all fantastic. We got some Fanny Bay Oysters to start which were fresh and very tasty with the generous amount of toppings. We also got some clam chowder to share with the table.

As for mains, we got two halibut fish and chips, seafood linguine, and the Signature Seafood Boil. They really don't skimp on portions, so come with an emty stomach! The fish and chip were nicely seasoned and crispy, the linguine was perfectly cooked and wasn't overly rich, and the seafood boil was fantastic with the extra butter and bread.

After the main, we were all very full but we simply couldn't say no to dessert, which was fried banana split that we shared. It was a great way to finish up the meal.

Overall, it was a fantastic dinner and we will definitely be coming back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMB1M1mhTlCkLjDZpvuU1HvKlRIyKwKl3hUD6w0&fid=0x0:0x3b98d3acd65c808c"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"Pau-Lin Ngen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYux2bxmNndX1OIzJvZDMUqV3D_LnyzewmMivzJ6au-MZvmUjOoQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice location by the water and a good dog-friendly patio

Had the seafood chowder to start and the prawn pasta. Chowder was hearty but consistency was a bit thin and could be thicker. Prawn pasta was a bit bland, was supposed to have a lemon butter sauce but didn’t really taste these flavours. Sauce was also a bit thin, dish had a good amount of prawns

Overall nice atmosphere for dinner","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDcQm23Jv6MLXZ4HSWt6bJMJfyAbaCKp1qCg-6&fid=0x0:0x3b98d3acd65c808c"],"When":"2024-7-5"},{"Name":"Michael Tetrault","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUOblNGbdNZ4FfoMdwgRA-V8sixAEwnNyg7ZpUaoUxqov7wNyQphQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Float 30 was a welcome change to the fare in Port Moody, where we typically eat out. The outdoor patio by the docks give different vibe. The seafood meals we tried were all top notch. Very similar to what I'm used to along the Oregon Coast. If you don't mind a few minutes extra to get there, do yourself a favour and check out this out of the way gem!

And if breakfast is more your thing, don't hesitate to drop in for solid offerings there. But the star of the show is the Croffle. It is a must!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOhhR1IZWRs66K978jSmjwGw4piLhn34Z-XJQd&fid=0x0:0x3b98d3acd65c808c"],"When":"2024-7-4"},{"Name":"Maria del Pilar Suarez Bastias","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQkK1cDdFizHmaGH9DFuMtu2z2UU7MMo5JSmiYa2wnd1SKRiL1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent experience. The food was amazing, very well done. We had to wait around 20 minutes until the diner time because we wanted the seafood, but it was worth the wait. Beautiful view from outside.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOwNSpIvi3-l-PcM_9Q8cg4zgmxaSgzsAzwAX0X&fid=0x0:0x3b98d3acd65c808c"],"When":"2024-10-7"}]

[{"Name":"Gillian Joseph","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOKvzRmGNzjQstxBrYfbBmkYDH9JdHiLpCMjKcXmFbY9UBKvs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for dinner at this restaurant,  and it isn't disappoint! The atmosphere was very cozy and warm. It appears they converted
An old home into their restaurant which gave a very homey feel. We ordered the guacamole and chips, a quesadillas and
A burrito bowl. The food was amazing!! So flavorful, and tasty. This is some of the most authentic Mexican food I've had. The portions were a  very good size and the prices on point. We enjoyed some of their desserts; churros and chocolate cake. YUM!  We will definitely be back to enjoy other items from their menu. Our waitress was very lovely and friendly. ❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhBhWWFstZneCGHxk5QLle6a0Js_e0r3KvaSzr&fid=0x0:0x76490b558beba794"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXEs7OfSCjWtOW9M8jMuKBw3YBoYuC5KPR31YpLwDEi3xUYJ7vu=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The restaurant is a gem, we had a wonderful dinner experience. The server was quite friendly and knowledgeable. He wanted to make our experience great and it was! The food was authentic and so delicious: we started with shrimp ceviche, then some carnitas enchiladas, and steak entree. I would highly recommend this place. 😋 the delicious drinks🍹 just topped it off right!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO6XvQvFGUdHy0BuSI4uVTIU6DqVqKkkn-Z68Mo&fid=0x0:0x76490b558beba794"],"When":"2024-8-12"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Amazing white sangria, and nice sip from my husbands piña colada. His prawn and rice dish was delicious.

My fish tacos were only memorable for how wet they got. My fingers were covered in sauce and the fourth taco was so soggy it fell apart and I ate it with a fork.

Service was disinterested and not warm.

Dining al fresco was a treat.

All in all, some things were great and others fell flat. I’ll try it one more time, maybe in the dining room.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMYNQP8yE3Xbu7-VoVF0X_Q6-gu5JsCDIdYjLUR&fid=0x0:0x76490b558beba794"],"When":"2024-7-20"},{"Name":"Marnie Eudela-Umlas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXg_gVRD_Hd9V3XIUh6_P71KHCryea9xsHYGqrZHTuXW_jdxEU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went here last Saturday for an after dinner get together with friends. Love the feel of the place and service was friendly and fast too. We will definitely be back and this time with our family:)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZRqnw_bIXLxzGLCvAs05rhRtpTDEkA-3RiB1w&fid=0x0:0x76490b558beba794"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"ladan ghafouri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVQKWEx_YV_Uj80v-xctgsLSGRY6V78hw5KMb4aNvRdZAaXJWti=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow! [{"Name":"Nancy Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_94zzTXxyiloKEVIGEZMIl3YYDzeOKg_OlxLIktGWc93WB4B6-A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I absolutely love two dishes from this restaurant: the roasted lamb neck and roasted lamb shank. The meat is incredibly tender, and the flavors are authentic and delicious. The taste really stands out!

On weekends, they even bring in DJs and dancers, which takes the dining experience with friends to the next level. The atmosphere is always lively and perfect for a fun night out. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPp5HOdfk5z0T6NKi5iaoSuPgdQP6pQaNSaGULT&fid=0x0:0x52b096151a2bb9c2"],"When":"2024-12-3"},{"Name":"Eva Zia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJp1CScTOq-jdIBVBA-K4f_r74TZU-kRd9MclConVIiSCPfy3Y=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Khaghan Restaurant in Vancouver is one of the top spots to enjoy traditional Persian cuisine. The restaurant’s beautiful decor and welcoming atmosphere bring an authentic Persian vibe to the experience. One standout aspect of Khaghan is the quality of ingredients and the authentic flavors in each dish, which reflect true Iranian culinary traditions.
Their koobideh kebab is particularly exceptional and widely regarded as the best in Vancouver. The perfectly seasoned and tender koobideh, grilled to perfection, is a must-try for anyone who appreciates authentic Persian kebabs. Combined with fluffy rice and fresh sides, this meal is an unforgettable experience that truly captures the essence of Persian cuisine.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMj2wHnWS6ubHZESyq0jgBU3JKTW-373pluYlzE&fid=0x0:0x52b096151a2bb9c2"],"When":"2024-11-5"},{"Name":"Mahboubeh Soumeeh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYDdZF0EYITzpASuc-GUgL3D-zOrPB5fdS08Hx_bFKpgbd83Da=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The staff were friendly and polite. This place has a good atmosphere from decoration to music. Our meal was served very gorgeous and tempting like restaurant in Iran. About the taste of food we have ordered, we expected more in compare with the prices we have paid.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPe-jNyU32uotbIEKqbVOnelQWZgqiKBKUBFjmn&fid=0x0:0x52b096151a2bb9c2"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"Rana Askari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGiquaWdZZatUPMrkajAAOOReXikqtkW7mp94Z7-kKODiThKc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food, amazing presentation, and a cozy atmosphere! The kebabs were tender and full of flavor, perfectly paired with saffron rice and crispy potato tahdig.
Friendly service and attention to detail made the experience even better. Highly recommend for authentic Persian cuisine!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqOOT3VzDnzQyC9XyICY9BAtktLHerO6sVuTT3&fid=0x0:0x52b096151a2bb9c2"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Ashkan N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGC9QpVpAYzkuU2nETbRxXDGZW6ZxU4DFK0Bytd5fdamCstw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great new addition to Port Moody! The food and service are excellent, just like at other Khaghan locations. The staff are friendly, and the food is delicious, offering an authentic Persian cuisine experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFYxPT6ZVw1VGTFPz9_w63g2Kv4IviL05zyoEh&fid=0x0:0x52b096151a2bb9c2"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Fox hmp","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQDamDUP5o_LpyAHYzMLSTM2wh8oeibxwZqA9_fJNfLvrII5o=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best koobie in Vancouver so far! The service was really quick and the server was friendly and nice! We also ordered the gheymeh and tahdig but the gheymeh seemed stale. Overall i recommend the place specially in weekends with live music.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmf9zfJgQf-y1tG-yWvagAHKvURm3kH9Mg_DWr&fid=0x0:0x52b096151a2bb9c2"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"MORI N.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmh-25mC5oA1PFMMA_52ysg1xmB302WDBqAM9LeMqrXCsb_9pPTA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"For The Record: 0 stars.

Environment: Dirty.
Food: Terrible.
Service: Unprofessional.
Atmosphere: Flat.

Ok....here it goes....

We were sat with cloth menus that were covered with dirty food fingerprints from the previous guests....(see pic.) Even the Number Stands were dirty (see pic.)
Why are there Number Stands in a restaurant anyhow? Did I by accident walk into a food court?
Moving on.....

The pita bread that comes with the appetizers was hours from having gone bad....I mean..the mold had packed its bags and on its way to us ....quick.
To call what they called "Kashk e Bademjaan" is an insult to the dish...it was more like canned goo...enough said.

The "Tahdig Mix with Gheyme and Ghormeh sabzi" was an absolute disaster.
The "Tahdig" was one layer of pita bread dipped in 3 gallons of cheap oil. The "Ghormeh Sabzi" was mostly red beans and the "Gheymeh" was mostly just lentils and tomato paste.  Honestly, I don't even know how to put it into words....and that rarely happens with me.
Moving onto the Mains.......

The "Loghmeh" was so tough that I jus stopped eating. It was so dry it was hard to swallow and unseasoned on top of everything. Why didn't I mention anything to the servers? Well...let's just say I knew that I would've been received with a combination of ignorance and indifference.
That was the vibe of the servers in general.

The Lamb Shank was covered with fat that is supposed to be removed with this dish. So, there is just blubbering fat covering 1/3 of your plate, instead of tender lean lamb meat on the bone. The dill rice was overcooked and all of it was unsalted and unseasoned.

We asked for Coke 0 and got Diet Coke. No glass served. No ice served.
Moving onto the desert. We thought maybe their desert will at least finish with a positive note.
They had 1. Bakhlava. If you serve their Bakhlava to either a Turk, a Persian or a Greek.
They will throw it at you. It was not Bakhlava. It was old, off-base, and an insult to this delicious middle eastern/mediterranean desert. Sad.

The atmosphere felt and looked cold, detached, bare and neglected.
Neglected of attention, care and love for business.
And boy did it show!

Honestly, as someone who loves dining out, who classifies customer service not be only crucial but an art, and as someone who has been fortunate to know good food and drink.
This is the first time I have felt disgust. Walking out of a restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMt_wnL0tUhqHuCNHtwYovEwovlBlL_H-mybsTf&fid=0x0:0x52b096151a2bb9c2"],"When":"2024-7-13"},{"Name":"Keyvan Mehdinejad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPKzxijUeOtNim64JgPdbBSKrIVKryIYCDBwjA01BPuXC_Cy8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had an incredible night at Khaghan Restaurant! The food was exceptional, the staff were amazing, and the live music added a wonderful touch to the evening.
Many thanks to the team for making our night so special.
We will definitely be coming back soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPU0FVAXRVr87dvF9ZUlwPaR4Gb-xLdw1c7HQc&fid=0x0:0x52b096151a2bb9c2"],"When":"2024-6-16"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Smsm","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJahhHpQ49rPywFzntGSRJCKfw5fN8vmt9No1wfkvKOTaluBg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time here and won’t be the last!
Amazing authentic Egyptian cuisine.
Fresh ingredients, very tasty and reasonably priced .
Nice family owned friendly restaurant with great environment.
That’s the kind of food quality you go to and you he kind of places we need to support to keep running .
The lamb Fattah and liver plates are exceptional!
Koshari was amazing !
Rice pudding was so yummy !
This small restaurant will grow tremendously in just few years and I won’t be surprised if they open a bigger branch somewhere else.
Great start and keep up the good work!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-_mCTq7ApaKl7NBP7S5oOlC9bMweeKiw80HbD&fid=0x0:0x51b1a026105e78f1"],"When":"2024-6-17"},{"Name":"Jordan Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW11-xeEA0Ih57ocfphXt0C50QwI614ll6t2qknklEqHoDt3aVy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Brought here by a friend who wanted to share with me what authentic Egyptian cuisine was like, and it didn’t disappoint! I’ve never tried this type of cuisine before, and I enjoyed everything I got to taste! My favorite was what I think was a beef brisket in a clay pot, as well as the koshari which my friend told me is a very traditional and familiar Egyptian dish. Glad to have had a chance to try the food here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvlKjavrYpXl2BDFJZ204fajM0-fFQkb7CPDER&fid=0x0:0x51b1a026105e78f1"],"When":"2023-12-24"},{"Name":"May Kassem","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDds0ieiZUI6Yi0FsAVLtR66A2hzOM_rjbQye25c-d40a2q1xQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was such an amazing experience. Especially as we were celebrating Eid. As Egyptians, we truly felt at home. Delicious Koshari, Beef liver sandwiche, salads, dessert roz be laban (rice pudding). We missed taking photos of Eid special which was Fata with lamb shanks and meat.

Truly amazing!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMBwbBurs4pDAI0ekaxxvf8hWWSIJFApI-3WEaV&fid=0x0:0x51b1a026105e78f1"],"When":"2024-6-16"},{"Name":"Ahmed Abdelhafez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8DusVaO3FCBTSFGaH5ZbeK6MEki7o3fDGNLPXKvCNe6BvCb8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sweet Egyptian restaurant. The owner and his family are professional and friendly. Great Koshari bowl!! Tasty and delightful. I enjoyed the liver wrap and Shawarma bun. Lovely service and atmosphere!!
Highly recommended to try!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGXA_bvJVwBJtTZOovBXGVAiAjKfXkkam0VJsD&fid=0x0:0x51b1a026105e78f1"],"When":"2024-6-3"},{"Name":"Mohamed Abdelhameed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1Fw7Iey5TWqjQKhgp4cxjkDc8IY73vpkeyPM2w2IdSwn1yp8T=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing authentic Egyptian street food finally in Vancouver!

Our whole experience was outstanding, the portions were great, the taste was absolutely delicious and spot on quality.

Also the the owners are extremely nice and friendly :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNov1B63BZclnQq6vEqAozKUjwRQoOeKClB215u&fid=0x0:0x51b1a026105e78f1"],"When":"2023-3-4"},{"Name":"Fahmy Elraie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUCTbgauEgVAcyhDhDjqVCMfmM6aO_K6KqW1LQB4qnb4zRHbT9P=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This authentic egyptian restaurant is a family business that provides the most authentic food from Egypt. Koshari is a must try dish which is a vegetarian dish but you can add to it the meat shawarma and it would be on another level of deliciousness. Also, I tried the tageem meat and potatoes in rich red sauce. Portions are so big and the place is small but so cozy, warm and welcoming.
We tried also beef shawerma wrap which was so yummy and packed with flavors.

Definitely I will go back to try other dishes from the menus.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMrYT9w02-x--XUWy6cL_g8pyuY_Fd8GM1Kr1A9&fid=0x0:0x51b1a026105e78f1"],"When":"2023-10-23"},{"Name":"Khaled Amin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6m-hYSKmlu7-vTr3aYKb_7-sM6f7xW3hdNZEmHB4Bv-lPtSHCDw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Honestly, the food here is delicious. The portions are great, and so are the prices. If you've never tried Egyptian food before, this is where you should - it's incredibly authentic.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"jon Au","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKWbBdUl-p7RPtX5Gqv7Cbn2UkHByB56iHiGOxfMYv-x0KI6w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time having Egyptian food. It was tasty and healthy. The family there helped me with the menu and shared their favorites. Lovely family run restaurant. Will come back for the tanjin and platter. Had the hawashi, with their homemade tahini. All their sauces are house made. Will come back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPdfyFoXu0H35j4K5_Gcb9JYO0irV1ft0Wnnbof&fid=0x0:0x51b1a026105e78f1"],"When":"2024-2-25"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Daisy Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVu1nxOTin_LouqpMg8SuZhcgesKimL_02BtAAmRSIlR4zjoDPR2g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"You have to reserve and order ahead of time at Henry's. The menu is constantly changing. It seems like chef likes to try different things constantly but the trade-off is that there is a lack of consistency. A dessert that you like last time might not taste the same the next. There is a lot of care put into the food and service of this restaurant run by a sweet couple.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-q6zJivd1CL2zzFfrr1DchcwIVKvsH_EDj7mi&fid=0x0:0x158418d9d6891755"],"When":"2023-5-31"},{"Name":"B W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJp85P5JohieEKJOfTMzyjH1aTNit_eIhBL3dFVyxf0xS2BxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Missus and I have driven by Henry's Kitchen many times on St. Johns Street and always wanted to try. We were happy we finally did.

Jasmine provided exceptional table service and tended to our needs. She has a very friendly demeanor and we had a nice chat. The food is freshly made after you arrive. One could taste the high quality of the food preparation. We thoroughly enjoyed our Caesar Salad, Crab Cake, Linguine Pescatora, German Pork Knuckle, Tiramisu and Chocolate Ganache. The homemade bread was a good way to start of our meal.

The restaurant has limited hours. Reservations are required as well as preordering your meal to avoid food waste. There is plenty of parking in the area.

We would highly recommend for a nice evening dinner.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSdv88ZgQm9qtGBG1FxL08P4IFiM_SDP2nj4pO&fid=0x0:0x158418d9d6891755"],"When":"2024-1-21"},{"Name":"P L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdkQ26g4o3dvVCWU9ihtXPpJaS5QpzFy1cxMTo4qJB3Lj-Rw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Exceptional service and food. From reservation to dining in, Jasmine was extraordinarily efficient with communication and  excellent with her service even decorating our table with a happy birthday sign and confetti! She was extremely attentive and made my party which included a toddler feel welcomed and comfortable. All servers should learn from her. She was so kind and caring to my toddler even when he was running around. The food by Henry was all beautifully presented and delicious with different elements of texture and flavour and perfection in terms of doneness of our meats. We look forward to more celebrations at this gem of a restaurant!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ali Pourhadi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX2iXVISnnHvJyKbaIf5Y2ya0kPji3HgqAXHVvDJ4VAf-MjLkg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If possible, I would give 10 stars. I made a reservation at Henry’s kitchen for our anniversary. They had arranged a very beautiful table for us. Food and desserts could not be better. Great service and a nice ambiance","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMANAae1CWeLWOflBXXLBrT4NNuvOGXroeyrU06&fid=0x0:0x158418d9d6891755"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"Cora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9YQmsmKhqCSvMVPAZKT18eImIWQ2QjEOLJi24FjTkNMSIg53C=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Henry's Kitchen is back open for dine in! Make sure you make a reservation via email with your preorders because that's the only way to get in! Everything was cooked perfectly and large portions for French cuisine! We had the duck breast, beef wellington as mains. Escargot and house made bread as starters. I highly recommend the duck! I'm so glad they're back open for dining in as ordering to go just wasn't the same. We will for sure be back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMDWuLgZexqbvRkmEGWeWCxqaoHBDFeJxMiTR0&fid=0x0:0x158418d9d6891755"],"When":"2022-4-5"},{"Name":"Dan Yang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWn20SO-hez6CdOPY0et6YJIfsXqZVK2JjuFROy8lc6ciazjVwLCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our group reserved a table here, we also pre ordered few days in advance. Food doesn't get prepared till everyone in your group arrives. The food was amazing! Presentation was good and the taste was good. Service was amazing. Desserts were great too. Nice cozy little place with nice interior. Parking is around but may be tough depending on what time you go. I highly recommend this place! Thank you Henry's Kitchen!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMBQPTpY9z9iVFVEqgOq7HvWAYBv54mYL1lVVE9&fid=0x0:0x158418d9d6891755"],"When":"2018-11-12"},{"Name":"Dave Cameron","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhpdoAj31MMy3I4viRnxDZTmsnr5-27AbISuaFHBaKYcNQJ78n=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"In a world of Cactus Clubs and Earls' restaurants like this are sorely missed. It is not the best food to be found in Metro Vancouver, but it is very good and a good value for money. Service is outstanding.

The concept is very interesting, instead of spending 10 mins pouring over a menu; pre-ordering like this makes dinner all about dinner. Also nice to be eating freshly prepared food rather than something made yesterday and warmed up in a microwave or stovetop.

I really like the atmosphere, self-decorated rather than the usual restaurant ikea furniture. Pictures and drawings from the past instead of a TV showing yesterday's sports highlights. Place is about the food and about the dinner.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Justin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVslDT3IjpBSLKbUfPD64hmIByw3PZ3A7YKnhNaaweMTcLb-EE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here for dinner with my friends. Everything that we had was very tasty and fresh with rich flavours. I got the Lobster Taglierine which was stunning and my friend got the beef wellington which was perfectly done. The the service is excellent. Highly recommend and its important to make a reservation in advanced if you want to go and we ordered in advanced too. Will be back soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdkQW2M3YNy_2--tuQGG4c4L8rHzntwTiqtUrP&fid=0x0:0x158418d9d6891755"],"When":"2018-9-22"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Katrina Mugume","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUg4hbo7JkWzLggVrl8uArdYOMwKzFL-5QANrBjFi8t5JdWO0ZY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This cute restaurant in Port Moody was ideal for my birthday celebration! The house-made pastas were excellent, and they even had a vegan option for my friend with an egg allergy, which was a thoughtful touch. The team handled our group with patience and class, making the evening feel effortless. With its cozy, moody atmosphere, very chic tableware, it was the perfect spot for a memorable night. (And they were open on a stat holiday) Definitely coming back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnptDkvMHY_17JDUXugxT9zpSjlGhz0482tyMV&fid=0x0:0x381a5196dc8558a1"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Joanna Fahmy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJTznlA_q5Xa6Whv5wHF-yEDXEyOSOXOXBiPU7xtZRDBuF4Yw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This restaurant is small yet a gem in port moody! The food was spectacular, very rich in flavour and very filling. I normally do not like red sauce with my pasta but this is the only place where I loved it. Definitely recommend trying it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPX0s-FehTmBIandsqUScm05VFf30b8vfaYGvyp&fid=0x0:0x381a5196dc8558a1"],"When":"2024-11-15"},{"Name":"J.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmjhttZ6CEnCJtI_oJCHP6y28cT1EohJbLRbH0VPc4zlBzwLlf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My family and I recently enjoyed a delightful “family date” at Osteria Povera, and it was nothing short of exceptional. From the moment we walked in, we were charmed by the restaurant’s intimate setting and the warm, inviting ambiance—it felt like being welcomed into a friend’s home.

Every aspect of the meal was exquisite. We started with flavorful, beautifully plated starters that set the tone for the rest of the evening. The mains were equally impressive, each bite rich in flavor and clearly made with fresh, high-quality ingredients. My wife and I enjoyed a wonderful selection of wine, perfectly paired to complement our meal. Even the freshly squeezed orange juice for our daughters was a thoughtful touch that they absolutely loved.

To finish, dessert was a treat in itself, rounding off an incredible dining experience. Osteria Povera made our family night memorable, and we can’t wait to return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMBorn2H8G2rXPQ6HNBvzKMFbVPm8frK4QvoDWe&fid=0x0:0x381a5196dc8558a1"],"When":"2024-10-26"},{"Name":"Amanda Aikman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1Y84gKptEn9f1Pr_kR4MSbhLFIPsVeNdzXf-aAkBDC2UttiAA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a lovely double-birthday dinner. Very warm and inviting, nice intimate space. Service was lovely, food was very good. Salmon was especially nice. Will definitely return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIJ6WTuDU3QpEMuCQeHAEreT2EvkG_GwLE_4x2&fid=0x0:0x381a5196dc8558a1"],"When":"2024-12-21"},{"Name":"Kyle Frank","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXc5mvvHuVJy-HJPmXkz5QhI2aB5vzHShD4aT_jgiLD2w_hJenzhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stopped in for lunch with a friend and had the place to ourselves. Staff was friendly and helpful. She suggested some lunch items that were not on the regular lunch menu which we did end up ordering. Food was very tasty, including the dressing on their side salad!  Will definitely return again in the future.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQEfJvxD7ZegMcxVrPRWkXFtqPntv9LWfl2nYL&fid=0x0:0x381a5196dc8558a1"],"When":"2024-12-4"},{"Name":"Jess Burnham","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWplX7jdDHi3IrJ66cTBexSohCr_MPgtnHzhO484KVFyy3eX5bLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Osteria Povera is my favourite restaurant in the entire city! We've been going there every couple months since they opened and it's always a perfect experience. The designers totally nailed it with the vibe, it's a gorgeous midcentury look and feel which shines in the summer and is super cozy in the winter. My go-to is the steak tartare and salmon linguine, it's out of this world and I always leave so happy and full. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPMCEvD76VNmhufnbMqtiuPXO9dHxFg61qXjgdx&fid=0x0:0x381a5196dc8558a1"],"When":"2024-7-29"},{"Name":"Kate D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWucZ5Kjxx4x-E5tJFk6phmF701csH13_pOauHoiwFMtKRubzIc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fantastic. Menu is thoughtful, with traditional standards and contemporary faves. Service was spot on and delightful (thank you Natalia.) Even boxed up my leftovers, I didn’t know anyone did that anymore. The wifi was a little weak and the a/c too cold, my only suggestion to look into.  Best of all they take reservations, no more lining up in the rain. They took a beloved old spot and made it better. Hard to accomplish, kudos!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtT82XXx5kZXGV-hqP95YdtEtXaA9Ti64pdzIs&fid=0x0:0x381a5196dc8558a1"],"When":"2024-8-13"},{"Name":"Aranza Jacobson-Sanchez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_WWY0ab4y-15qDrT4kd3uC_Yu81Vo85HPgzwUkt1QdqPzo-s=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We went for our anniversary and were very happy with the taste of our food, specially the lasagna. It took about 25 minutes to get our dishes and there were only 3 other guests. Service was okay. No changing station in the bathroom for babies/toddlers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMcETlo2cNgTsOpCdZubBGQb3C8ufeauxF6RWJo&fid=0x0:0x381a5196dc8558a1"],"When":"2024-5-24"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Champagne Kingdom","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWT9L6nbhgKeVF6uvC80gh6he8ZgVExYxBb0bRQFJovbeiruBo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had an amazing experience here! We stopped by on Saturday to enjoy the patio and savor some delicious beers - the Mexican cerveza and sours were our favorites! We also ordered mouth-watering brisket from the food truck. We loved it so much that we came back the next day (Sunday) for their breakfast special, which was not only delicious but also a steal at just $8! We highly recommend this place!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfEk-c1QAmpyXpVqdrVvl9WAKt2iFj3uzEE9WI\u0026fid=0x0:0xd7f40b1afa25f995"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"Meagan O","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXsIpETfJCnO9swLQBZUTKHiE8RdzaCfMqoS1jEt2QgcgkZNi0L_g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We hosted a reception for a funeral at Trainwreck Brewery. My beloved mother in law loved pubs and live music so this was the perfect venue. The owner Chris was an absolute gem to deal with and was more than willing to let us use the space as we wanted to with decor, a mix of food that we brought with food available at the brewery and a beer cheers to my mother in law. Anna and Max were our servers and were absolutely wonderful and so attentive. Mike on the Mic played some renditions of classic rock that my mother in law would have adored. Looking forward to visiting again on a happier occasion.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkXKOhLdL3MGDe_p4AhYEL6Mblp9v4_bRaEwqz\u0026fid=0x0:0xd7f40b1afa25f995"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Ruby E.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTXhvN-EpNac4Qr_mgdf5IDJLY8uKSuinXxuVkhfUtlVyIdrlu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for the flight of sours ($9) - a great way to sample a variety of brews.  Also tried a couple of the meads, which aren't available less than 12 oz so you can't sample those in a flight but both the Orange Saffron mead and Lingonberry-Elderberry were delicious!  We happened to be there for the live music and the guys performing on Nov.1 were very talented and provided great ambience.  Best to reserve a table in advance for your friend group. For hot food, you can order burgers, poutine, Mac \u0026 cheese from the on-site food truck, but i recommend eating at Sushi Modo or Karumba across the street instead.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMoNQKV3pgdoxqg10PinoLS5tfdkIJJH4yjRr85\u0026fid=0x0:0xd7f40b1afa25f995"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"ANTONIO TOTAN","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKCtjigHEHqTcQK9K0HpS0C6AQPHd5Ae_UDjB1Vt_RFtE3Lrg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I celebrated my birthday at Train Wreck Brewing and it was an extraordinary experience! The atmosphere was perfect, the staff was very kind and attentive, and the food and drinks were excellent. All my guests had a great time, and the music and decor complemented the evening perfectly. Thank you to the team for an unforgettable birthday! I highly recommend it!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"A.J. Canadian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0mITu_1OR_MuXzhVIkPjHjZnimy2Y-mI64r72OA1Zbucah6-N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Train Wreck brewery in Port Moody is spacious and has a good beer, cider and mead selection.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFMSPDPKxPVuV3eUqO4TA56VugToIT5JGvhSlL\u0026fid=0x0:0xd7f40b1afa25f995"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"H S Madan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTu4oMkDk1Z3MjNV_7rONLy371tsTTJL-xX0jcQ-rhkA8blIkVlg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Stopped by to have a few drinks. They have a very large selection of drafts on tap. At the present time there is nothing that you can buy and take home. But the server said it will happen soon. I also ordered some cocktails on tap. They were extremely sweet and not very strong so if that is something that you look for the new would definitely enjoy it. Personally for my taste it was way too sweet. They do have a barbecue truck outside that you can order food from. We ordered two poutines and the poutines were really good. This is a very nice place to hang out. They have an large outdoor patio and a large indoor seating area. The servers are very friendly. The patio that is up front is right on the street so you do get a lot of Street noise. But you are in the Sun.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPkBI3MZpIjEPBjne5BJ5sSz1o4QNvZ_nN98esD\u0026fid=0x0:0xd7f40b1afa25f995"],"When":"2024-4-16"},{"Name":"DJ Robichaud","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUpMQna8Vc_nXWe_E4gkarRFa-7vGEALVmsnGeLEYoQVG4M4q4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The live music they had was so warm and entertaining, and the staff and I were not stop laughing and enjoying each others company. I am not an avid drinker but they have the best craft cream soda I have ever had! It is a must try!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFjGzci_I2jfYDZ-1ERLp22KCkjJgFyhLNVtru\u0026fid=0x0:0xd7f40b1afa25f995"],"When":"2024-2-19"},{"Name":"Mohammad Ghorbani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXLhM08Ep2NCTojfd1QxmX4qnCTzzQfI85j3VW30xREciyNrcn6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I finally found one of the best breweries in Canada! They serve an excellent hefeweizen that could easily make them one of the top breweries around. Any Bavarian missing a good hefeweizen should definitely come here and give it a try. They’ve also been recognized for their British pale ale, which is outstanding.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnXDKkTETrmKC-lqIhQMKRCRZEZnpQpihjHbkr\u0026fid=0x0:0xd7f40b1afa25f995"],"When":"2024-11-14"}]

[{"Name":"Brittany","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWHTcuSM-4ly1uIP3q2-jgQ_2Vqi7GhBmGO9JykCcOlnN1NYOmqYg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A bright and lively spot, Yellow Dog has a large taproom with outdoor sections in the front patio and large backyard.

We arrived mid-afternoon on a rainy Saturday and the brewery was almost completely full. Definitely a spot you’d want to hit early if you were looking for a table. The beers are pretty standard - lots of pales and IPAs, nothing super stand out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMB8O8Ak583hZ9Ry9Rr19LnqCSA49y4GMhqp1S3&fid=0x0:0xcd9537764d3594b0"],"When":"2024-11-13"},{"Name":"Terry Magnusson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUFrUSmySzcWvY6tmyVD3D1lN7ojKGuONRx8vPyoU3T_yUfDBmk0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My fav beers being an IPA, Pale Ale type. Wide open space, relaxed atmosphere, backyard outdoor seating. Wide selection of drink types. Super cute 4 oz glasses for higher octane offerings.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNThnmTKtzsKJ7qajmfZoBeo3JsLBVBmSljhUIT&fid=0x0:0xcd9537764d3594b0"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"Bryan H.W. Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVgK0PWdG96lejWVSXO7AO1Tq8e7p4LLAcXWbR2PL5p1IPe1L68=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Yellow dog has great tasting beer and open space for sitting. They won couple of bc beer awards. Worth it to check them out. Taste clean and nice beers. Chase my tail is pretty good!
Limited parking space and street parking you need to pay now.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYXAJPl3lzSuZ7QMGk_0GHNtyQ-E9oCrXw4zFE&fid=0x0:0xcd9537764d3594b0"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Edit: less than a week after my first visit, I’m back with my husband. We sat on the patio in the back and there were some many children it looked like a birthday party. Bad parenting meant some were running around screaming. My Lager was good once again. We shared a Mama Said pizza. Nice afternoon except for the feral children.

My first time here and it was great! I had the Jessie’s Amber Lager and it hit the spot. We got a table in the back and it was long enough to fit our large group.  Not much interaction with the staff other than ordering my drink. I look forward to my next visit as the first one was so fun.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOd57rvWH31leDk00huvjtTHDKBf_IdFT2X7aWu&fid=0x0:0xcd9537764d3594b0"],"When":"2024-6-29"},{"Name":"Rafael Couto","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXyo5TKanWNHEDHXb1Gq6KCmpFB7KdMoGBT_G2HM-SghKElwajZiQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great atmosphere, good beer and fair price for the space and comfort. Sometimes the line was a bit long but nothing that compromised the positive experience.
Great choice!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-4Ylp60rDhAT7Wrw9b-BlUc7tabPjt-XozuF6&fid=0x0:0xcd9537764d3594b0"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"John M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWItgijJKwgA0f52g38y2veJk-Ddfx32Y6n5pRa8jqM3m7RR0lStA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Summer weekends get very busy but I came on a weekday and it was quiet. They have decor that fits their theme. They've embraced the industrial look! The place is kept pretty clean and tidy.

Most beers they have on tap are brewed in house and they have a good selection (like sours, IPAs, pale ale, etc.).

They've got an outdoor area in the back which I prefer over the front patios of other breweries along the strip. It's a bit more private. Though there is a train that runs in the back pretty frequently which can be loud and annoying if you're having a conversation.

Would recommend overall.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQdXSwYS9EQyeqHUxptYBZrmypqZArOB8SpaZU&fid=0x0:0xcd9537764d3594b0"],"When":"2023-6-9"},{"Name":"H S Madan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTu4oMkDk1Z3MjNV_7rONLy371tsTTJL-xX0jcQ-rhkA8blIkVlg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Yellow dog is a great place to hang out and have a few drinks. I've been here a few times now and always had a good time. The bartenders behind the bar are very friendly and helpful in making selections and offering suggestions of their menu. Had a few beers and a few cocktails and everything was very good. I would definitely recommend this place if you are In the area. I also have a great selection of cocktail menu and the margarita was really good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZZXY5Nzww1IPaj7yOhdoJHqqWGvAZJIWEpCqo&fid=0x0:0xcd9537764d3594b0"],"When":"2024-4-16"},{"Name":"Kevin Ardron","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVCL8y2rmGEfyT0TJ5qeAIKKwS1t3AoTRChuuKefhZLJItZ-yc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love this place. Not only is the beer amazing, but also all the tasting room employees are extremely attentive. Brooke, Jackie, Kiera, Phil, Mack and others are so friendly and really care about the experience of each and every customer. I have seen so many customers come in with obscure wants and the staff always bend over backwards to meet their needs. I can honestly recommend Yellow Dog Brewery Port Moody to anyone who wants a great tasting beer served by great people who are always available for great conversation!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Kel Shaw","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxlG7dSzG0XCaRucFdzjLtGXMN3t4REtRn-uT0qJZlGy2kASSN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Stopped by this place on our way home from the lights at Lafarge. Beers were very tasty. Hubby and I both had a flight and as we were a bit hungry. Ordered a pizza. Pizza was nothing to write home about. But. We most definitely would come back for the beers. Young lady helping us was quite lovely.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOthVoq5Cfqk8XrCVAAzuZSxg1Y9Tpham0rxhE&fid=0x0:0xe0355d35af341a71"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Munro Stuff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWj0Wcuk6ox5dfAeJ4fAaMbhX_F-nzzt3p5oc_f0hBd0NpbGSM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice addition to Brewer's Row. Fabulous patio with a view. Great selection of beers, pouring more than you see on the website - Bass Brew Apricot Plum Sour was a nice twist to the usual. Non-alcoholic beverages, plus snacks and pizzas. Bonus vinyl onsite! Definitely worth stopping by.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOosvPYW55_BqPErAF6g4PlAhi3aU6yrnBcKCp9&fid=0x0:0xe0355d35af341a71"],"When":"2024-6-26"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Enjoyed the atmosphere at brave brewing and they have some tasty beer options as well as one cider option. Seating is available both inside and outside on the patio. You can see the big tanks where your beverages are well. Food options are mostly pizza and small bites (tater tots). There are also non-alcoholic options. This brewery also hosts a bunch of different events throughout the week and is very lgbtq+ friendly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO5rN9aafJSF8OT8LpccfsfEIRg2nejD8BsKLJ0&fid=0x0:0xe0355d35af341a71"],"When":"2024-5-12"},{"Name":"Kishi Malhotra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXp7iQ5Uf7Un-XaXqZWvHP20ufS7JCMx4Fl5wwp6Ya3rqJRQtqn5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Really nice and roomy place with a lot of good beer options.

Didn’t try any food but had their Cider which was really nice and refreshing.

A lot of seating and a good vibe.

Service was great, nice kind people..

Definitely coming here again to try more food and drink…","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIyTs4_gK1-M0WDmZTYPemL5RlVILuqFXYzskl&fid=0x0:0xe0355d35af341a71"],"When":"2024-8-14"},{"Name":"LeSean Goveas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKDRgTFKr4GrBr7AlgX8KTWNR7v1-RaAw3jWSGTGGzcPXWwv2Y=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Recently, I had the pleasure of visiting Brave Brewing, and I must say, their covered patio is a game-changer, especially on busy weekends when it's bustling inside. Opting for outdoor seating by the fire pit added an extra layer of charm to our experience, although do note, the heat from the fire does not spread much so you really need to sit close by to feel the warmth. We indulged in their signature brews, the Stiff Upper Lip and Guts and Glory, both of which were delightful. However, the star of the show, the margarita pizza, unfortunately fell short of expectations. It lacked the crispness we hoped for, and the sparse basil leaf placement provided a comedic touch. Despite this hiccup, Brave Brewing exudes a cozy ambiance, making it an ideal spot for couples seeking a laid-back atmosphere. Overall, it's a decent establishment, with the potential to shine even brighter.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMCnEiUFjLv0HHr2x65aiDoF0hM5tnnN1Mfq1OF&fid=0x0:0xe0355d35af341a71"],"When":"2024-2-27"},{"Name":"Jacquelyn Johnston","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLfy_pLzvat08k9FzqYD-5djtqo3UfUv3fLgHw-FhXMEBTZ9A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I always dislike having to write a bad review but I was disappointed tonight and hope management is open to listening and improving.
Unfortunately my list includes overpriced wine (thought I was at the airport for a second), poor service (even though I tipped the server never checked to see how my pizza was), the most skimpily adorned pizza I've ever seen with some pieces literally having none of some of the advertised toppings (although the flavour was good), and a dirty bathroom that doesn't look like it's been cleaned since the last time I was there (note the baseboards). Thankfully the musicians were entertaining so that was good. It looks like there is an effort being made to make the place fun and inviting but it needs some tweaks, in my opinion.
EDIT: In response to the manager's reply I want to say that "advertise" regarding the pizza was a poor word choice so my bad. What I meant was the toppings in the menu description. I don't recall seeing the word Neopolitan on either the table or wall menu or the website. From reading other reviews about the pizza, I think adding Neapolitan would be helpful to manage customer's expectations. And suggesting I go to Fresh Slice for a loaded pizza felt like a dig. Or maybe that's a poor word choice also. The comment made me feel that the manager's attitude is, If you don't like our pizza, go somewhere else. Trust me, I will. One less Brave customer.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bean Around","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWNELTFQVdO24xebFKof_HuKCneX2V-u6QoV-a7eVRLVdSz7lUy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Brave Brewing Co in Port Moody is an absolute gem! Their craft beer selection is top-notch, and the inclusion of kombucha is a refreshing touch. It's become my go-to spot for winding down on a Friday afternoon. The service consistently impresses, and there's always something intriguing on tap or in the works. If you're seeking a vibrant atmosphere with quality beverages, look no further.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOku1hDzxf9VuZQzte9omisbYkzCnF9LwgqonMm&fid=0x0:0xe0355d35af341a71"],"When":"2023-10-8"},{"Name":"Victoria S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMq3ff68oLE1cp0u8ig_8JgVOkBu_OL2K0cJoeXiTRzO_2-1Sa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We took flights to try different types of beer.  The general opinion is that I liked the dark Bold and Beatiful and the light Manha Dry the most.  Although Hefeweizen is also not without charm, it is quite fermented.  Grace Lager - too watery for my taste.  And they can't take beer home either.

PS.    Thanks for your generous offer.  I wanted to buy a draft beer to take home.  Unfortunately, the saller answered me that they do not pour it.  If this is not so, I will gladly buy from you what I liked.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFKAKPwB2Ztwc_MqzCpAHFIzFHKJz9fj4nPDt8&fid=0x0:0xe0355d35af341a71"],"When":"2023-7-2"}]

[{"Name":"Kanoko Hara","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUe-kRTpDihBfLa8xRSgzMJcSdgMTMMYCzNVnqFRK33YxtGEzQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As a 100% Japanese, Sushi Modo is my absolute favorite place to eat. They make the rice just right. Not squishy, not hard. They also make the sushi good with that perfect rice. They don’t squeeze it and it has the perfect balance. I love their atmosphere. After a busy day at work, all you want is a quiet relaxing place with good service and food. I have been coming here for almost 2 years now. Please try it out!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgLgldQ1OaPUsZ6vp9UJLPDh0N_8Vmkdi5Sr1l&fid=0x0:0xfb79f340c93969dc"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"Lucas Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9NXgPLNobBkdSwF_7JloE6MmQ8sxnfrIYGRkUNQjXj1cwm3qc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sushi Modo has been my go-to place for sushi for 10 years, from the service to atmosphere this restaurant is top quality.
I highly recommend this place to everyone in the area because their Salmon Oshi is a must try! Good food, good service good atmosphere, five stars!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOlMPg32mYQW90P9Hz_tfYZBFy3KDOD9ZTsOz2O&fid=0x0:0xfb79f340c93969dc"],"When":"2024-8-20"},{"Name":"Miguel Palma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL2dg5fhwUTVpZDs5xpjNM_RibIKbGyPyVUkblyAtz4ZM5Rng=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have been going here since we moved to Port Moody 2 years ago. Ever since the first we’ve had it, it’s become our go to spot for sushi.

Staff are always friendly and attentive.
Food has always been fresh and on point.

Overall, would recommend for everyone to go!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0UYLx-5p5Vt4POlhQXvUjwjiyJxeokCJ4esxo&fid=0x0:0xfb79f340c93969dc"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Hannah","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGuhpfwpzD-OpsxB7LuhoJPSBqAxcRsc2yP5kJJBKy7_7Ccy0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Sushi Modo offers a wide variety of interesting, delicious rolls and specials! They were offering a free Salmon Oshi for Google reviews (which was a great way to maximize the meal but be wary of boisterous support). The Mango Tango roll was a big hit and the service was instantaneous as we received our food within 10 minutes of arriving. Overall would recommend a visit if you are in the area!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdeuRAlP_NucakBp_Y282P69Ixw6ajAbhWKWy9&fid=0x0:0xfb79f340c93969dc"],"When":"2024-8-31"},{"Name":"Honghong Kou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJyski_wMu1-c2VtLnTng_8ezOmdvy8Y0tjCN1kRlU3LLPNRA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It’s easy to find this restaurant. The roll is very nice and yummy. I like mango tango roll. It includes a lot of things. I really recommend this kind of special roll to everyone who comes here. The people here are also friendly and nice. They are very welcomed. We will come here for dinner again. Really a nice place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMiuai4x-DG6UEj0Gdu02_8Js0C3anKBR275VmY&fid=0x0:0xfb79f340c93969dc"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"Huang Recca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIDF647f8wTC9xYKRRSNQV8CPkQJrc1Y81nFNPZerRiknh_jw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food was quite good and they go cater to the little ones. But, for a quiet friday night with not a few tables. It was quite challanging to get the server's attention when we would require any additional assistance. We were just shy of walking over and gdt the water pitcher / additional napkins ourselves.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNv19BUMM6p1k2RLY6IzHPKDU-i8GaQRUQanM6A&fid=0x0:0xfb79f340c93969dc"],"When":"2024-7-28"},{"Name":"Ruby E.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTXhvN-EpNac4Qr_mgdf5IDJLY8uKSuinXxuVkhfUtlVyIdrlu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My new favorite sushi place in PoMo! Prices are reasonable and quality is good. I like that ordering online for pick-up costs the same as you pay if you eat in, but expect it to take longer (over an hour) to get your food if you order Friday night.
Recommended: Mamma Mia Roll, Chicken Karaage Roll, salmon oshi sushi, miso soup","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOf_Z0aKUMRVMYSkre1Bc1C-28X6esBR9csALP2&fid=0x0:0xfb79f340c93969dc"],"When":"2024-11-4"},{"Name":"Ali Kamali","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKIIurODPUbCpAoirgeBGPcWw0N8tQnXY0o6sKq7u-jvOVEkw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is our favourite sushi restaurant in the area. The fish is always very fresh and the portions are generous. The service really great and the food comes out fast. Really love the ambiance too.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkgMmYaXFnqf8u3JS5boZ6HPdziLGHGbhclDjI&fid=0x0:0xfb79f340c93969dc"],"When":"2024-9-15"}]
