[{"Name":"Jodine Morehouse","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkI3ILmstAY-XeAWqv2CETEpjWiJVODW602jRpnYogrvfslqk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I can’t wait to come back here again! Such fantastic food and a fun environment. The fried chicken was top notch and the waffles were some of the best we’ve ever had. The breakfast truly felt homemade and with care. The kids breakfast was a great size and my kiddo was very happy. Service was okay; you can tell the servers are very busy maintaining a constant flow of customers. It was efficient and we didn’t have to wait overly long for our food. We did have to wait 20 mins to get a table initially, but we wrote our name and number down and were called when our table is ready. There is plenty of free parking around. This has the be the best breakfast I’ve had in the tri cities.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKJgj8sWDLDS9qegVktaFJLY6wHAIH52u_I1Iw&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-8-27"},{"Name":"Christina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAZU__kcA5bzRg06Xj5DBBJ8cZ62N3LvOHAgj11jS16XxVPZvg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a good brunch. Can’t say anything bad about it. Not to pricey and the serving is neither big or small. Customer service is superb. We’ll definitely go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPvn0YrbOK9PQexBbmH0uzrLD7g4XyCGtU_9RmR&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-10-3"},{"Name":"Maria Fernanda Mejia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIuRq66bP7uwZvuWOAzrXMaIaP65fNk1AbmES51ho5i654OFOA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is the best place Ive had brunch in Vancouver. Food was delicious, the place was so cozy and had the perfect temperature. I went with my sister and we share the Benny Eggs with cubed potatoes fries and pan cakes and hot chocolate. Everything was so tasty and well done, the eggs were pefectly done and the pancakes werw so fluffy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOrT4XQKDGK2dJViD6VsKyNO0Zqf0UnFIb9_9w&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Korean western breakfast and brunch joint located in downtown Port Coquitlam. Lots of exciting dishes to try with Bulgogi dishes being the most exciting (Bulgogi Benny, Bulgogi pasta, Bulgogi sandwich, etc.). Service was a bit slow as the restaurant was busy. We had to wait around 10 minutes after we put our name and number down to get called. Food was good and presentation was impecable, but the taste was not particularly memorable. The door of the restaurant was open so it attracted a lot of flies from the outside which wasn’t ideal and really made the entire experience not super great.

Interior decor is very interesting with a lot of Lego input.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4awtX1JY8GFBJy9bWY0sS6Pd9fHU7-n1sKPpK&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"Daniel Jung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFE7g6vnjf23CW6mDeh4anchF8fxBs6O5Nsx0bvhepuO3MVzWa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great brunch spot in the center of Shaugnessy. Came in Sunday around noonish, luckily no lineup. Food took a little bit but was definitely worth it as it tasted great!
Seems like service is team based? It was a little confusing who was taking care of our table. Overall great experience","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPGRk5-xoM7MNas2Lf8X9-8tL5TPa1NyfeG2t5K&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-7-8"},{"Name":"Helena","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiYVJyd2ntFwLRumbYS9Kznuj6jXHoPn0UkQ_zdJDM29rWiQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It’s easy to find the small and clean restaurant on main street in Port Coquitlam downtown. We ordered a Bulgogi Benny and a Corned Beef Skillet. The portion size is quite large. I love the soft and fresh eggs that danced in my plate. The pan fried potatoes were crispy on the outside and tender on the inside.  Overall, their food is so delicious and service is great as well. The only downside is that the food is too salty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOodTPBFYt_-JZobr-pvtMCbt6_xvN_fc6G6khW&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-6-20"},{"Name":"JESSICA","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVB2i5CpRP7UX8-wv47l2MrFmMz2VuMLPi87EdWVFtliHFbqvwR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cute spot, warm and cozy. Reasonably priced and tasty. Benny’s made on sweet English muffins/crumpets versus traditional. Potatoes very tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNpj7mBBwvQ0YWcrdYBHVE_81woZdvdFQHDUKKA&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Mike Liu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL20X_OxbcK6Mq4LfB8wD0MzYN5bZWaRAXw5XJobEo4cGthsw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love how everything is flavored really well and that the Korean fusion element is delicious. I got a simple 2 eggs with sausage and hashbrowns. Everything was done really well. Note that the hasbrowns do have a layer of onions as a filling. The cubed potato’s were delicious.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzoRfYSvHs4qQ-gqmZ89EYwZ0drtW3HbqfgRVO&fid=0x0:0xa167a404bce0a118"],"When":"2024-7-11"}]

[{"Name":"Michael Taylor (Battleship Cobra)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqj0B3uXJEI4-ToxfQ2z9_jzbT_Ue49f5Zh-XFyFN013RMY27V=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great atmosphere, awesome local beer selection (Yellow Dog, Parkside, Phillips...) and an amazing menu. The yorkies with the horseradish mayo are my favourite (nachos too with house-made chips). Grab a beer here with friends when the breweries close!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJA36R5ySOUBseh08jwYaauoI6WbHMcuq6cwEM&fid=0x0:0x9e56d5642c4facf0"],"When":"2024-10-12"},{"Name":"duane r neufeld","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhhlb1lcJQnDlyAPy1R2d_GOddZm-jMhyJJsiO9YhD02HRj38=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow a bit of a time/space warp.  If someone blindfolded you 10 minutes before arrival you could be thinking you are in remote Ireland ( though I've never been). Love the seats, decor, dark woods.  Ready for a fiddle and Fife to start any time.  Delightful pub offerings, wide bar choices.  Keen to revisit!   Consider parking in the nearby  underground.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Delany Bramley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIK2uPQopfYgNbDujVOD83GTVPgHurczGu-am82p4W8WqARQOg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The chef actually made a shrimp wrap rather than chicken for me whereas at a pub on Coast and Praire in PoCo refuses! The Well didn't even charge extra! Well done! Service was great too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyNfcHzYO_EJe8y8qrUyXb0YJemgmOi9TBsut2&fid=0x0:0x9e56d5642c4facf0"],"When":"2024-11-6"},{"Name":"Grant M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRWL_i5cZiVpXExK1H8xMkwx4_6CHC_xRkP2HoYZIVJehiW1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's been a few years since I've stopped in at the Well.  I decided to walk from the Eagle Ridge Hospital as my brother was getting some tests done. So rather than sitting there and waiting I decided to go to the Well.

It was a beautiful day out so I just sat outside and enjoyed a couple Phillips Blue Bucks. The beer was nice and cold, and definitely nice and enjoyable on a nice day.

I grew up in Port Moody ( Born and raised ) and when my server came out with my second Beer I told her I can't believe where I'm sitting right now, that it used to be farm land and Horses running around and so on. I used to feed the horses at times with a carrot on my way to Hockey practices as I lived and grew up right behind the Esso Gas Station just up the road from the Well. My server couldn't believe it actually.

It's always great to come back home, and enjoy and reminisce the days of growing up in Port Moody 😀","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPv3oJO4DpTTTLZeliGYdyfWDrnkEZCqhuceeSF&fid=0x0:0x9e56d5642c4facf0"],"When":"2024-6-20"},{"Name":"Ebrahim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPIKcLlYsRXzj_NU-cKrILAfiV6rHoottOnSl1Co3QI6YN1537=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Let me tell you about this gem of a local restaurant! The food? Absolutely amazing. Hands down, I had the best burger ever in Vancouver there. And guess what? If it's your birthday, they'll hook you up with a free shot as a little celebration gesture.

But it's not just about the food; the vibe is just so darn lovely. And then there's Megan, our server extraordinaire. She took care of us like nobody's business. You can just tell she adores spending time with customers and making sure they leave with smiles on their faces. Her kindness and professionalism are off the charts. We were asking for this and that, and she was more than happy to help us out every step of the way.

And get this – despite being a local spot, they're rocking a solid 4.3 review. Can you believe it? That's on par with big names like Cactus Club or Earls. But honestly, with people like Megan on their team, it's no wonder they're killing it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvo0dNJ8HHPdioG2-C9fSqlxrS1i8lXecWQHVT&fid=0x0:0x9e56d5642c4facf0"],"When":"2024-2-17"},{"Name":"Chris “WolfmanMac” MacLeod","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXk7iYkhOaOdtR5BVdCsDim4y9lHdV_5Fftj-CQxRzae_zANkHr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"4 stars for food only because this is not really your typical pub fare.....so don't be disappointed with potato chips as nachos instead of tortilla. Be absolutely thrilled you can get baby Yorkshire puddings stuffed with beef so you can have it all in your mouth at once instead of knife-and-forking a nice meal at Grandma's!
Typical burgers as well, but their salads are awesome and different as well. A couple of beers while you choose which game to watch on numerous TV's and a working fireplace. This place rocks for a beer or a sit-down for a couple hours.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kyle Desjarlais","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrRBEamWMJl4icWTFU6lImngzC0ND5A_dzd32uf-Z4ExMBsyw-Kg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow.
Beautiful Irish pub !
I lived in Port Moody way too long before I found this place. It's a real hidden gem.
Of course I had a Guinness on tap and then a Jameson on the rocks, proper drinks for an Irish pub. It was busy. Very loud, and very busy. Definitely a very lively and popular place.
Service did not lack at all despite the full house.
Props to the top notch bartender killing behind the counter. Really enjoyed my drinks at this pub.
Cheers.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8UXOiylz8Pos0QiZelUGmaw9Ik0WSZC46yT4d&fid=0x0:0x9e56d5642c4facf0"],"When":"2024-3-6"},{"Name":"Golnaz J N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwh094AvMjRiNSQoo9HjnFTPUMh8c3XSGOFZ78okUlI4KLdqnN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The fried pickles and potato skins were absolutely delicious, a true delight. The price for happy hour was incredibly reasonable, making it even more enjoyable. However, I found the beef in the sliders to be a bit smelly, which was a bit disappointing. Nonetheless, the overall experience was great and I would definitely recommend visiting for the tasty treats and excellent happy hour deals!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPobWxLhOj-eqFVY9uuXuOOAVwOHIGg8p3L0sK_&fid=0x0:0x9e56d5642c4facf0"],"When":"2023-8-27"}]

[{"Name":"Dan Yang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWn20SO-hez6CdOPY0et6YJIfsXqZVK2JjuFROy8lc6ciazjVwLCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were staying at the Poco Inn for several days and we decided to try Izba. We had gone once last year for breakfast and wanted to try other things on the menu this time.

Food is absolutely amazing here. Service was excellent. We dined in and did take out a few times. We can't wait to come back to dine in when we visit BC again. The Pork Hock was amazing and I had to order it twice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkeN1QD0k77gLzuWNTChtSslZ8MsYKszhisKyY&fid=0x0:0xc4417d5c6f1e0d7d"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"Ewa Jagla","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJt2Lx4cSyXVMUtHz5GqW2QX5giQiHT25H1LY2KPyEyH86PMQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious food freshly cooked from scratch, awesome atmosphere, superb customer service. The best place to have Christmas party as well as small gatherings.
Highly recommend 😊","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhWkgmxDtyb6rEjrVCF6m82pasIw5N0DVS3SmQ&fid=0x0:0xc4417d5c6f1e0d7d"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Angela Jeffery","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtGyld6d4wIU2Lb7oe7xsoiq4r77iaBdF6nkFQ8ek01eF1q7c=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We ate here as we stayed at the hotel for work, and I may come back to try some of the other menu items, based on the compliments of the others in the group.

The server was pleasant, as well as enthusiastic and knowledgeable about his menu recommendations. He was courteous about checking in and giving us space for our meeting.

The seating was comfortable, and even when it got busy at dinnertime, the ambient noise level still leant to easy conversation.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqeLGhHKnP50PS663FCp_-g_jpbS2XjZyg9vTH&fid=0x0:0xc4417d5c6f1e0d7d"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"Laura Thomas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJ1taLWiLR5Kqy6TcBzB6ZWgyoj4UBO3ZptGvBaE7P-Aow2HBl=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We visited Izba last week and while it's a regular in our family gtg's I'd be remiss if I didn't brag about this terrific PoCo restaurant, with its cosy, modern, diner feel. They have booths and tables and they can easily accomodate large groups.

I am hearing sensitive and I find the noise volume in this restaurant to be perfect for my needs. I can hear my company's conversation, while not being too quiet. It's a great place to eat & catch up with family or friends.

While they have a terrific  breakfast & dinner menu, we usually visit at lunch. While we've tried many delicious items (shout out to their pierogies, schnitzel & cream of carrot soup!) we tend to have our favourites on their menu. Their chicken tacos are a huge hit with our family, although I lean towards their chicken club sandwich myself. Yum!  And for the late in the day breakfast lover amongst us, the brie & berries stuffed french toast is ah-mazing.

This is a great lunch spot with great service and great food. We love this local gem.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOR6It5KMGfKdXdWFlwEe9CsEMI6164BfCS_2qP&fid=0x0:0xc4417d5c6f1e0d7d"],"When":"2024-6-22"},{"Name":"K Kunz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJritYkEeakN5S6DMeaooDNRMG4rg18kYdKvuJy7Hp_4TwqoG2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was our first time at Izba Bistro and we loved it! Our server Brenda was great! She was nice, attentive but also let us sit for awhile. Food was excellent. We started with the battered brie that came with fruit and a spicy berry compote. I then had the spinach and feta chicken and it was SO good. I loved that it came with spaghetti squash as well. You don't see that too often. My partner had the Vienna schnitzel with an egg on top. My partner being Austrian said it was different than what he's used to, but still enjoyed it. Lastly we had the sacher Austrian chocolate cake and that was also really fantastic! We definitely will be coming back soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTHEmdhYUMMgbRx5jBghp47Wwy64aw3PImFw7B&fid=0x0:0xc4417d5c6f1e0d7d"],"When":"2024-4-22"},{"Name":"Varoujan Makdesian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKfL2mqaxtwIkiG0HlyGX_xrPtFgM36rEWRUZvaEgqUWz0Duw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"****AVOID AT ALL COSTS****
I was really excited to try Izba, given its reputation for authentic Polish cuisine, but unfortunately, my experience was far from what I had hoped for.

First, the service was extremely slow. Despite the restaurant not being very busy, our server seemed disinterested and hardly checked on us. We had to flag them down multiple times just to get basic things like water refills.

The food, which I was looking forward to the most, was underwhelming. The pierogi were bland, lacking any real flavor or seasoning, and the filling was far too dry. The borscht was greasy and tasted more like something that had been reheated multiple times rather than freshly made. It was also way too salty, which made it hard to finish.

The manager/owner, when I raised my concerns, was dismissive and unhelpful. Rather than apologizing or offering a solution, they seemed indifferent to our experience. It’s always frustrating when management doesn’t take feedback seriously, and it only made the situation worse. It felt like they weren’t interested in improving their service or maintaining customer satisfaction.

Overall, I won’t be returning. There are plenty of other places offering better Polish food and a much more welcoming dining experience. I would not recommend this place to anyone.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tones Jyler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKK4GXgTVLnajqhYm0hfamOs6EgRB-CcfZKNyrEZSlfbU3odg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have driven by this place so many times and wanted to try it. Really glad I finally did and you should too! Had the platter for 2 and it came with everything in the picture for 47$ (2 potatoe pancakes that are so crispy and delicious, polish sausage, a huge amount of perogies with lots of chopped bacon and sausage to go with it, 2 large cabbage rolls, salad, and some kind of carrot mango salad) me and my wife both left stuffed and our baby even had his fill too! It was so delicious and you can tell everything is home cooked with care! I highly recommend it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNF0XwsVtW1OfgUUiRRKbghfLTu0ovz1VSWdmvU&fid=0x0:0xc4417d5c6f1e0d7d"],"When":"2024-7-6"},{"Name":"Kat s","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2PheeHlSTOrgESZq7PphUL-4YpUmC6odPCrLoBmlFoDLLyzPn=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had breakfast almost every day here while on our trip. Service was great, waitstaff was kind and accommodating of food allergies, and the food was always high quality. This will definitely be a spot we continue coming back to whenever we're in PoCo!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPKp-lMImM02uuFAI1z4isRNhCXkLkbDt4Yr4Xj&fid=0x0:0xc4417d5c6f1e0d7d"],"When":"2024-7-22"}]

[{"Name":"Sarah Okut","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLTH-O9yHrUXXSzwuweULzXw1pBbME2AVL3wPUzYMdoLT_dRg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Pizza Pietra and really enjoyed their pizza and San Sebastian cheesecake. The pizza had a crispy crust with fresh, tasty toppings. It was delicious! The San Sebastian cheesecake was the best part—it was rich, smooth, and creamy, with a slightly caramelized top that gave it extra flavor. If you love desserts, you should definitely try this cheesecake!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3wU0_wer5w028bhetbEqdDgTlTPAd9mr8aiH5&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"Mucahit Mert Alagoz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUlZFzlr8OmJ6ReNSeqILjiXkPYOR-Wi6HlJhjaTTE_xGsRl7kohA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I really loved this small and cozy Turkish café run by two Turkish women. The staff is very warm and friendly. Although the menu is a bit limited, the breakfast options are quite delicious. I loved everything, from the sucuk (Turkish sausage) to the eggs and meat-filled pastries. For four people (we ordered a bit too much), the total was $105.
I definitely recommend it—a lovely café!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZkVllSrfsqQVnk7-eaCEQy80caDFl6QFecd6N&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"방새단Jp","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPRFl5X_2oRYVKyp5YOzyZvBiFq4LXRAXvUH4K1gSFuhrTkvIu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered the poached eggs with avocado.
They took a while to get the plate ready, but it was much better than what I had hoped for. Ingredients were fresh, tasty and I would definitely come back again","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPW5MCUo0Kn75oa42Blt_gR0Ah7EI2gXYUVdZhL&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-11-6"},{"Name":"Mahesh Vanga","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_R99DIUm3YNCVBnH6ipuMklk--v4TSFTsQ7Tybr4ECj_qR-ZP9A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is by far the best pizza place I have ever been to in the Mainland area. We explored this place as part of checking regular pizza places around, to our surprise this has been the best random pizza place ever been in fact the best pizza I ever had in the mainland area. Any food/pizza lover cannot miss this place, they got a wide variety of pizzas to offer as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO263l3lNZQ04gOHPrnihMubx8QyholXqUTO6DE&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Graham Sutton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL8UeAA1nmB6Ej3WgCR3VioNDAdhDivzoWDT4UCyjNTsgC4MA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Breakfast was awesome!  Traditional Turkish meals with lovely fresh bread and Turkish tea.  We'll definitely be back on a regular basis.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODmWArQZDzyV5LCBa5m3uJi_01rXQ5LyF0EMno&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-11-20"},{"Name":"Onur Kaan KOÇ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLl3-LHlkDHqQOafBmwY6xCPBlOCHVa2JkVR6DeNJcaxq3QYw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Clean, Happy and delicious Pizza Pietra, siezed my day 😋

At first I was hesitant because of the mixed reviews but I really wanted to give it a try, especially because of the praised stone oven and authentic dough.

I've been to most regions of Italy, ate a lot of very good pizza and I must say this pizza restaurant reminded me the times I was in Mediterranean.

You must use good quality ingredients and have precise dough craftsmanship, and have the right oven with the correct temperature to make a delicious pizza. But every body knows, in our modern times, this equation is quite impossible in big cities because of the cost and profit concerns.

But in this pizza shop they nearly got the perfect combination.

They have a real stove oven at the right temperature, good quality ingredients and handmade authentic dough.

Both pizza and Foccacia are nicely crusty and juicy. The Tomato sauce is not bitter nor too sweet, just yummy and fresh  ;-).

Toppings and mozzarella have a very good price to quality ratio.

All the ingredients are really really fresh 👍

A suggestion for them, I think you should make a pizza with different ingredients which are hard to find in PoCo

And for me the most important thing , people in this pizza shop are really happy, hospitable, positive and energetic. They really smile to you because they just want to. The total vibe is just like the warm and welcoming family owned pizza shops in Italy too 😍😍.

Ps: I asked the owner to tour the kitchen because of my cleanliness obsession. And yes he let me to quickly tour the kitchen and I'm amazed, this is a really really clean kitchen for BC standarts 😉","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODw8DnBQZ_EDJZzRNN9UlLF96GZOid--UDy1PJ&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2024-3-28"},{"Name":"Aamir Sheergar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTKU4wfuc0kwoyEwJxy3N-nmGgBy-VjbHs41hImisM4pU2gpbxyQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great pizza, loved the thin crust. Friendly service from the ladies in the kitchen. One of my new favorite pizza places.

Also tried the cheesecake, it was not too dense and had just the right amount of sweetness, a great balance.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"M. Murat Kucuk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQxmakxls5MdK3S6o9QjUak841XsiEQ7PpJlT7cOAjNN9ECiE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Prepare to be amazed by this extraordinary pizza haven nestled within town. Without hesitation, I wholeheartedly recommend this remarkable establishment to all pizza enthusiasts. During our recent visit, we indulged in their custom 2-in-1 pizza, an exquisite combination that left our taste buds in a state of pure bliss.

The staff at Pizza Pietra were not only kind, but also exceptionally helpful, ensuring that our dining experience was nothing short of perfection. Their attentiveness added an extra touch of delight to an already exceptional culinary adventure.

Do not, under any circumstances, allow yourself to miss out on the opportunity to visit this exceptional pizza establishment. It is an experience that promises to tantalize your senses and leave an indelible impression.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPoC8qGLwQyu83S1THS9PbLQVeSXqTbUxjDY8X&fid=0x0:0x4640aee62581d2d2"],"When":"2023-6-25"}]

[{"Name":"Leon Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPOnBvlGz2k_WzxOhCiURR3aRaAE5ffHXfUBJJ4GP7GBC5Wn8K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A cozy little cafe/brunch place with plenty of delicious dishes to choose from! They've got a nice portion size and we especially loved the way their toasts are made. I highly recommend their omelette :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZ5K-Qmil3-5FfOu3HV6suOUB5_gTZaSdx6lXR&fid=0x0:0xc5b1d5425c13c8b1"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Joanna Fahmy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJTznlA_q5Xa6Whv5wHF-yEDXEyOSOXOXBiPU7xtZRDBuF4Yw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came here for breakfast, food was decent for the price. We were surprised by the cheaper prices compared to other breakfast places, our plates each were between $10-15!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMzu-Xt_jxAyTGDfs4rTT284gusElPuQMtjRPS0&fid=0x0:0xc5b1d5425c13c8b1"],"When":"2024-11-19"},{"Name":"Joanne Shih","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXximxdR2J0MX38SMpQXvX83o69PGyHXNObNbbK0mDK-tz8T9Z6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cozy neighbourhood brunch place! Came here years ago, I had a pretty good overall experience. This time revisiting, it’s as good:) Have lots of options on the menu with pretty good prices. If you’re looking for an easy layback weekend brunch with friends and family, this is the place😉😋","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAEYQcbo_wZ58s9yrSFOG1879NJa2cpm6b4Dzw&fid=0x0:0xc5b1d5425c13c8b1"],"When":"2024-4-28"},{"Name":"Chanelle D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXCEGtGi_rnAXcez2UGfi8tPvkrtnC3uoCyaDz_NpX-tJAfWp2A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great little local breakfast place in downtown PoCo. I like supporting local businesses especially when you see them trying so hard to give good service.  Food is delicious and if you are looking to take a break from cooking, this is a place to go. Many familiar dishes for breakfast and brunch. The prices are very reasonable so tip well. The portions are sufficient. Good value and easy on the wallet. Fast service. Great for walk in because parking is a limited at the front.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMC2XT0W0I6LPk5xzrNiIq7KCmlFqE6wzuS3_ZZ&fid=0x0:0xc5b1d5425c13c8b1"],"When":"2024-1-8"},{"Name":"Imran Cuttilan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKz9vHOBlaUTXNDsWXAFrX2NjKnPFKZDmrrx2BKyP3U2hXEVQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Don't be fooled by the outside, this place is a great find!
Honestly one of the best breakfasts I've had since moving to Vancouver. Don't expect gourmet meals, but hearty, well-cooked food for less than $50 to fill a hungry family of 4? Yes please!
It feels like a family run place and the wait staff clearly know their regulars. I'm almost considering moving to PoCo so I can eat here every weekend.
If I have one recommendation, skip the hash browns (fried potatoes are pretty much the same everywhere) and go for the wonderfully fluffy pancakes.
Cannot recommend this place enough.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chun Ho Lau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWeN6tyeslrX1zBXDjrKJdBmn-J6R7mrVei78Pf_EwSNa0qPEvB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This place is great for the price that you pay. Never did i imagine that you can find a less than $10 breakfast and with this amount of food. Swiss Sandwich with fries was great. The pancakes and eggs and sausage was good however next time we probably won’t get the sausage as the bacon on someone else’s table look better. The pancakes were light and fluffy. The hamburger steak and eggs - hmmm. I will skip next time and not great for 14.95. The pancakes and eggs and sausage was better got less than $9. I did change a hamburger for two sausages with my wife so the pictures won’t look right. But you can see the amount of food there is for such little price. It’s definitely a 4 star and I think next time I will find something that I will like to bring it back to 5 star. Not today though but close. For some reason they are not doing soup with the sandwiches so just beware. I certainly be back as there’s plenty to choose from.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPFN8PXpXtYRseN6e6FzlaSNbb833AYUq_pm39k&fid=0x0:0xc5b1d5425c13c8b1"],"When":"2022-9-10"},{"Name":"Emmanuel Carino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJ9g6OsewbE5PvEJQG0W2MrejjY87xqZcS0O_-lbnLLATuQeGq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Amigo Pancake House is a delightful spot for a classic, no-frills breakfast. The pancakes are perfectly fluffy and made with care, offering a comforting start to your day. The atmosphere is cozy and welcoming, making it a great place to enjoy a relaxed morning meal. The service is warm and attentive, ensuring you feel right at home. If you’re looking for a simple, satisfying breakfast without the fuss, Amigo Pancake House is the perfect choice. Highly recommended for anyone who appreciates good food in a friendly setting","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Yvonne Chow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKwIOIAqx6fGEXpwJ9wznPD-K-TC6RqVahvNzt21E-visP9PQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food may be decent, but the kitchen service is exceedingly slow. We were here for brunch - arrived at 1120 am, and we’re still waiting for our food more than 40 minutes later. This is for a table of 2 with no additions, sub-outs - just two breakfast mains. To be fair, they comped us a fruit salad but with other brunch options in the area, it’s not the fastest service for simple food.

We visited about a year and a half ago and had the same issue. Their kitchen management needs to be much better.

To be fair, it might be a weekend issue as my in-laws said they liked it when they visited on a weekday.

Probably won’t be coming back though. The service is lovely and we are happy to tip them well, but the kitchen management leaves much to be desired.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4xqBL2ofcHFLZBewBZKBDJPaSYa0OSM7cCuox&fid=0x0:0xc5b1d5425c13c8b1"],"When":"2022-10-24"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ruth Ruiz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTnu7xFYlP7rD5mwZkeARHhfeUaoC3PNXoHdON7a1-uORvpN9C=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love this coffee shop! I come here very often to buy coffee or dessert with my baby and even though I know it's not a Mexican coffee shop, it reminds me a lot of my city, since there are many coffee shops of this style and when I lived at home (Mexico) I always used to go to coffee shops. The girls have always treated me very well and the atmosphere is pleasant.

The only bad thing I find is that sometimes the heating inside the café is too hot. I travel in the stroller with my baby, very bundled up because it is cold outside and that heat shock is not very good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPo8pP5cas-3RLhGVySsEy3VRc01x1oZXFCyuuu&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"Anna Romaniuk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUr2AFtzmK4eynrxAD-4PxdacLbRpvj3wICA9-bMinTX39gnZ09Ag=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Kaffi Espresso Bar is a delightful spot for coffee lovers. Their flat white with oat milk is smooth and perfectly balanced, a must-try for those who enjoy a creamy, non-dairy option. The macaroons are light and delicious, offering a sweet treat to pair with your coffee. If you're in the mood for dessert, the Pavlova is exceptional—crispy on the outside, soft and airy inside, with fresh toppings that elevate the experience. It is a cozy and charming place to unwind with great flavors! ❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMpYWnT378aHyXniTDPHBRbUMIQ1bsocPrG8TnJ&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Chloe Rachel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgExGuK1W-XgQc1tPnrQlqQkWxCTaNhdz977uVTTY3zjpsAzs-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Stumbled upon Kaffi during a walk in the area, and ordered a decaf latte. The latte was nothing special, but was good! I liked the coffee flavour and mild sweetness it had. Service was alright! There were 2 staff working and the one taking my order seemed newer. They had to confirm with the other barista which drinks could be made decaf, and what non-dairy milk options they had. Unfortunately, after the fact, I noticed that on my receipt, they charged $0.75 for my oat milk substitution (their drink menu board lists non-dairy as an additional $0.50).

On a Sunday morning, it was quite a popular place with groups sitting in to chat as well as customers taking out. They also have a selection of baked goods at their front case, including some nice looking croissants.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8YYm3abZx1S-ePK76QQqcNpY2l-G_LVUg67Tx&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"jasmimaria R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW4pJsI6zmjzg6T7Vv1nULcTI0hckuLuMTShtjT6u4cC-gzFPL6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Kaffi Espresso Bar offers a decent coffee experience with generally good service. However, the staff could be a bit friendlier to enhance the overall atmosphere. The espresso was delicious, perfectly brewed to bring out rich flavors. Unfortunately, the danish didn't quite live up to its appearance, as it was overbaked. Despite these small drawbacks, it's still a solid spot for a quality espresso.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwwA6O2uQcW6N72-BQDguSoLTJNsHUWJ0otUKO&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-7-24"},{"Name":"Golnaz J N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwh094AvMjRiNSQoo9HjnFTPUMh8c3XSGOFZ78okUlI4KLdqnN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice little café with a cozy atmosphere. We ordered a latte and an Americano. Both were decent — nothing extraordinary, but enjoyable enough. The service was friendly, and the place was clean.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgOhDNVbIXowAFL-2vv3wvZY87Bg4LO5cdvImv&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"Karla Vazquez Peniche","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUDz1KwihcBNerOeAGgbA_zV52UY14XSBM9ioRoz9zK0FXfnKW8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Kaffi Cafe is hands down my favorite spot. Their pastries and treats are always fresh, delicious, and perfectly baked. The staff are friendly, welcoming, and make you feel right at home. It's my go-to spot for a cozy atmosphere and a tasty treat. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNUGCkbaOTjJ7BqCvlziDZkHVQkgMslwHg_BA9E&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-10-3"},{"Name":"Ana De Pinho Gast","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW56TF2vLF5XxLTSdTNkl6pqTWOu6vdMDM2MLXOpO50vFcc7x3-=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Kaffi espresso bar in Port Moody is definitely a hidden gem in the area. From friendly and skilled staff, to delicious pastries and personally my favorite coffee in the area. I have worked in Port Moody for almost a year now and stop by Kaffi at least twice a week and I can definitely say they service and quality of their items is always consistent and outstanding in my opinion. I will continue to frequent this establishment. Keep up the amazing work ladies! 🌸","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM9Hdx7PvcBtMF0xrkwsS0l3wsz3S-27qOjX46Q&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Marcus L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZLCsGchamGOA-Wtg05cndL2yjt6EBGtYR9Y9cWGpcdNb3N09u=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I recently visited Kaffi and unfortunately, the experience didn’t meet my expectations. The service was disappointing; there was a mix-up with our order that wasn’t properly addressed, and the staff seemed indifferent, placing our food on the table without any interaction. The food quality was underwhelming—the mocha lacked the rich chocolate and espresso flavor I anticipated, and the latte was weak, missing the robust coffee taste one would expect. Overall, the visit was not as enjoyable as I had hoped, and improvements in both service and beverage quality are necessary.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP1xPAvd9_22vrU4mRfRgtuKPvrDnpes9hXFJ8&fid=0x0:0xada3e4e6eeb98ebc"],"When":"2024-8-10"}]

[{"Name":"Champagne Kingdom","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWT9L6nbhgKeVF6uvC80gh6he8ZgVExYxBb0bRQFJovbeiruBo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Get ready to indulge in a holiday treat that's anything but naughty! McDonald's has unveiled the Grinch Meal, and it's a game-changer. Choose from a Big Mac, 10-piece Chicken McNuggets, or McChicken sandwich, paired with the mouthwatering new Dill Pickle McShaker Fries. Wash it all down with a medium fountain drink and top it off with exclusive Grinch-themed socks. This limited-time offer is the perfect way to treat yourself (or a friend) to a festive feast.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXEC1iVoGPCHgyCK9_k_YbtN2Go-JeFiR3zw6d&fid=0x0:0xd94aa484324fb3a2"],"When":"2024-12-9"},{"Name":"Michelle Holst","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW3UHsn8v85uEc1ncaiXo7uwHjjPW4oaPuEW-95_FrHo_TpfKO2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This location is messed up! Literally just went through the drive through and they handed my order piece by piece telling me due to Port Moody law I need to pay for a bag. WHAT?! I have been going to this location for quite some time over the years, I’ve been there at least a dozen times over the past year, did the drive through last week. I was not asked if I wanted a bag at extra charge. This was a first. Who orders drive through and no bag included???? I’m driving home with loose fries sauce and nuggets. I am so pissed right now. I’ll repeat I have never once been asked if I want a bag for extra charge when ordering through the Sri e through. This was not asked when I ordered tonight. This is the stupidest and inconvenient thing yet!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3E0qLijN1TjN0_EyaWPAeaT-rxosNKxe108AR&fid=0x0:0xd94aa484324fb3a2"],"When":"2024-6-21"},{"Name":"Adel Raeesi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKgm5aNoXagV1gAlUcicldlywMBjiCuEVODWTF-vIYwywlW7w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I was very disappointed with my recent experience at this McDonald's location. I had to wait far too long for my order, and it seemed like the staff didn’t care at all. Instead of focusing on getting orders out, they were laughing and chatting with each other, completely ignoring the waiting customers. It’s frustrating to see a lack of professionalism, and it left a negative impression. I hope management can address this to ensure better service in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Raymond Blackmore","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV50ISsw20KNGusbrG20UKmZtsz-GtvLoXqyY0sfrOFC4GdcFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Deeply disappointed. I appreciate that 10:30pm isn't peak hours. But it's also not exactly the dinner rush.

Ordered a fillet-of-fish w/ extra tar tar sauce. Got a fillet-of-fish with what I would hope wouldn't constitute is even close to enough for normal tar tar sauce. Which sure feels like the the opposite of what I wanted. I'd give it 0 out of 5 if I could.

Pictures attached for proof. They labeled it extra tar tar and put next to none on it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM94DxVL3X8O80ZYuz8TpfusLXvCD39R18_kLvy&fid=0x0:0xd94aa484324fb3a2"],"When":"2023-12-9"},{"Name":"Shauna Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJVNM3Tt90W8QlMBtj9ifwj38hSJCnpt0WU0w5LvMsLZXYTEw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really appreciate how clean it is inside. All tables had just been wiped when I walked in making me comfortable to sit in. The floors were just moped aswell and the condiment stand and garbage clear. My meal was also great. Really hot fries and warm burger. I got the crispy chicken deluxe meal. The till person at the front was nice, had a smile and a good attitude. My family went through the drive-thru and we were immediately put off by the attitude of the lady taking our order. I ordered 3 3-piece chicken strip combos all with honey mustard and sprite, immediately after that she asked me \"Is that all?\" I said no and continued to order 1 chicken BLT combo with sprite. She then asks if we wanted honey mustard with both of the combos and I stated that it was only one chicken BLT burger, that's when she confirmed that we had ordered the 3 chicken strip combos. At the end of that she asks again \"Is that all?\" again I say no and order 1 double teen combo with root beer. After we paid, we only recieved three drinks instead of FIVE, we brought it up with the woman who was attending to us and she argued back and forth with us, we thought it was only the drinks so we just told her to leave it and drove off. When we got home we realized that it wasn't just the drinks but also we were missing the entirety of the 2 chicken strip combos. We went back to the A\u0026W just to realize that the lady had just conveniently gotten off her shift. Unfortunately, there was now a new staff member who had to deal with our anger. All we wanted was our money back and we said this quite a few times, this was a whole ordeal as well as he tried to offer us the chicken strips that we were missing. We finally got our money back and it's safe to say that we will NOT be coming back. All of this, not even to mention that the QR code on the window to let them know how they did was expired, as a result, this is the review you get, and the review that you deserve.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bachir Abba","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUm96VLPvjcmyOyqeAhQsyNGSJRyHGcLK49B2JWG8W3Q-Kg7wS6Ew=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice place to eat if you are in the neighborhood. Smaller venue, offers snacks in-house, pizza truck outside on my day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwOYfm-PYdK1e2rtht_cGbKOXmDCXbXx4LG-dS&fid=0x0:0xb1d5a4cd24e4928"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"Y. They are quite well established in pubs and liquor stores across the Lower Mainland. Although availability varies, most of the time, you can find brews on tap that are on the stronger side when it comes to flavor and alcohol content, which is absolutely fine with me. Space Armadillo DIPA and Juice+Cintra IPA are my all-time favorites. Their taproom is of a decent size, but not too big, and the staff is friendly and helpful. Also, there is always some sort of a food truck right in front of the brewery, so food is not a problem.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQsS4yvRNopVpxl8xx1LsYXer_yFGhILuRBa0A&fid=0x0:0xb1d5a4cd24e4928"],"When":"2021-3-10"},{"Name":"Steve Morgan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmgrmzSyB3CC_qWamR3pXmaZna6-RxfqDluiFzTGNrypDReGc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Best beer in the area. Great pizza truck out front.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8i5eEdX_oDSoguZdL3RaJF_H05WzY7L1AaUmb&fid=0x0:0xb1d5a4cd24e4928"],"When":"2020-10-15"},{"Name":"Alan Lensink","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiUwCeCmUetf71kEfPgC6rH5900gBIDxe7g76jUiL6IDj623SV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Twin Sails has an impressive line-up of delicious beers: IPAs, sours, stouts, lagers, ales, etc. I think they have a delish beer for everyone's taste.

[{"Name":"Ads","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwDyuvQtXP_VygmU1rNXhUJ0mc48E4h1QtDkdEfrlXmuS-mYhL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Bowl like Scottie!
For face value, you can't really go wrong with a Green Goddess Rice Bowl on promo with Subway rewards scheme is pretty solid. Yum grub, fresh ingredients and a good amount of healthy veggies and salad is dope. All this signed, sealed and delivered in completely compostable packaging has my respect and I love it. Subway really need to up their game on the veggie options with offering the bowls and subs an actual legitimate protein option, even some simple beans, lentils or a veggie patty would have topped this off perfectly.
The server was also super friendly at this chain, very approachable and patient, nice people.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVlR2LQRr5G6wVmdwgS-8f8BHXnjcgevyVZ1Rb&fid=0x0:0xef0f19180dea12f5"],"When":"2024-1-29"},{"Name":"Manjinder Gill","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrMESvQoTPFBSLHOnOdCGWtlTxVGGCIR2BrVQ67B5gnMOJ6dl2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Today around 11.58pm i went at store. [{"Name":"Mahsa Haghjoo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRSnT0Wip7Pbg6Z8m0cglGHkWd61YfkTkUIlG6b0IkPWIUcJi2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The staff are friendly, but they might not check on you often, so they may miss refilling your water. The quality and taste of the food are okay. However, the gheimeh stew on tahdig was served cold, some parts of the meat were still cold, suggesting it wasn't freshly made or properly warmed up. Kashke bademjon was beautifully designed. The menu offers a good variety of options. Overall, it was an okay experience, with some room for improvement. The portions are big, and there's plenty of space to seat large groups. Plus, there's free parking right in front.The decor is nice, featuring some traditional Persian carpets on the walls.

Totally recommend ordering the dogh. [{"Name":"Avis Woo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXh4Pb-SJt2DTMUggN2-tIRxEo8pAErRU5SI_TxM4gC-gvdVBym=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great movements my daughter and I spent here with great coffee, great hot chocolate, yummy coffee cake, wheat-free brownie and banana cake while waiting for doctor's call nearby from Port Moody Emergency Care Centre with 5 minutes walking distance! ❤️❤️👍👍🎄🎄","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFgWyPt5lRnzUcbw2ll9HyCR5HS5p4CRG77Ucm&fid=0x0:0x5197e6b12452f807"],"When":"2024-12-24"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cute cozy cafe for drinks and tiny bites. It wasn’t busy when we went on a Friday afternoon so luckily we were able to get seats and sit for a while. The interior is woody and there is a clear area to stand for ordering and waiting on your orders. There were signs posted that says it is a laptop free environment on weekends as well as 90 minute seating during busy times which are reasonable. Drinks are tasty but I don’t believe the hot chocolate was made with real chocolate. Street parking only.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMFwCsN9D9Rwioy9lI2Tv-iUgM1vRQ3eyakyzJa&fid=0x0:0x5197e6b12452f807"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Line Rejmers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0T1dg6KY3grV8k0ZQ4Ky-7ZoPCjPwiJ6glB3_yFoGHY2ex87HvQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely lovely. The coffee is some of the best I’ve ever tasted (highly recommend a ‘Spanish latte with a hint of orange’ or a ‘Sam Jackson’). Furthermore, the ‘Divano breakfast sandwich’ is super delicious. The location is in a lovely quiet area, and the atmosphere is super cozy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOABKnA-dMKT-TcN2BnYx_cgmIF_gKL8ztvTJ0U&fid=0x0:0x5197e6b12452f807"],"When":"2024-8-11"},{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Love the coffee, food and service. Get the peanut butter cookie if you can. Would be even better with some comfortable seating, I’m not a fan of hard wooden chairs. Decent selection of vegetarian options, and lots for breakfast, lunch, or snack. Great espresso and interesting seasonal drinks.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP778HgN8KVCPWAjlok8Bp_2AfVL6wnYIbSACCu&fid=0x0:0x5197e6b12452f807"],"When":"2023-12-2"},{"Name":"Sunflower T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIxJjMmucwwDA4tlzDMS42ioEJCCaNp6pZeLU1uC3v2pVpwoQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Since they close quite early (5p.m., which is a pity for no outdoor coffee in summer late afternoons!), we were politely asked if we would take paper cups when we arrived at around 4:30p.m. Although it would be nicer to use mugs, we had no choice but to forget environmental concerns for once! The cappucino was good though, so was the banana cake!

Next time we would arrive earlier to enjoy the atmosphere, the decor and relax more! (lap-top free on weekends!! And 90 min slot on busy hours!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfwJ8AOg1d5gQzOmY5tl7hMIeNZXllNvqtGMwf&fid=0x0:0x5197e6b12452f807"],"When":"2024-5-2"},{"Name":"Arjun Tyagi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWopm7CB27Brsn2nZf_ZcGMYA1rC2xZn0gFS2Ev_B4zUk8mX8MoIQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Honestly one of the best latte’s I’ve had in ages in BC. This took me back to my recent trip to Melbourne, Australia and their world famous coffee culture. Grabbed a to go latte in a rush this morning so no opportunity to take pics (beyond the cup with me) of the establishment but it was well laid out with a great coffee house feel and plenty of seating both inside and out. They also had a wide assortment of pastries and food items in general which all looked delicious, I will definitely be back and update the review with more pictures accordingly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_bV1SFQwNmBHl5YL-hQ4034IJLDttEoYYbnnX&fid=0x0:0x5197e6b12452f807"],"When":"2024-4-18"},{"Name":"Pradyumna Gujjar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVHYwZPoeWTWb_r-Pj3URXZmwvjMuE8IJLkPSR4xqAVv86CR0HjQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The ambience is great! The staff are warm and welcoming! They pride themselves on their coffee and I can see why because they taste good.
The let down for me was the chicken wrap. It was a bit undercooked and the sausage wasn’t that great!
I had a Spanish coffee and a spiced pumpkin latte, both of which were great!
The balance of the spices and the flavors were great and the pricing was reasonable.
All in all, would definitely recommend it for the coffee but might have to visit again to speak for the food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTJ1TZNjysDMIbZ18szw3LHfxb-VHSbGsxZzhZ&fid=0x0:0x5197e6b12452f807"],"When":"2023-9-18"},{"Name":"Jay P (JP)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWelLAg3J6-KSk1lMcsa257JZB2pUVD6ykaC4OdY8owoc_MOJyN0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Divano offers a charming and relaxed environment that’s perfect for working or unwinding. The decor is modern yet cozy, with plenty of plants and comfortable chairs. I tried their iced latte, and it was wonderfully refreshing and well-balanced. The shop also offers a variety of specialty teas and vegan options, which is a nice touch. The only downside is that the Wi-Fi can be a bit spotty, which might be a concern if you plan to work here for an extended period. Otherwise, it’s a delightful place to enjoy a cup of coffee.","Images":null,"When":""}]

But in first we entered by mistake in a lounge just next door, but somehow we figured out it’s not the recommended place by our friends. [{"Name":"Peter Ryu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIA1mPJxqbAq3sA5Yx2oELWcSP1BdJp83hRCQqxHH8j4y2zYQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for breakfast on Tuesday.
Service was good.
The food was so good. We had rice noodle w/ minced beef and parsley. Soup was hitting the spot.
Creamy seafood was good. Added some white pepper for seasoning.
The chicken steak sandwich is so good. Their chicken steak is a must try.
Great price, less than $30 for 3 items.
My gf and I left very full.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN4icTkTUUv9JDkn2JtXGDZMAMx_I3hwCSyteyy&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-12-10"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Peña","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing customer service—quick and friendly! We ordered the BBQ pork, shrimp fried rice, noodles, and meat poutine, and the generous servings lasted for days. Loved the ambiance and the extensive menu selection. Will definitely come back to try more items!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMv9VLbM7Eayn1Tn58vlSESqVHJeByNmFCEMrlt&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Johnny C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMH8aFZIGB5a7CFStbNQ6JGT0sYgxOttD7xMtIebcz8N9tnSzq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Typical Hong Kong style cafe.  Sometimes difficult to find parking because lot is share with other businesses.  Food is OK but prices have gone up a bit since the pandemic.  Food and drink arrive quickly.  There are some elbow room between tables unlike other restaurants that’s elbow to elbow.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPP9Yp6b7U-wMOA3h89pt4AgqSR2112vjBXwLXE&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"J T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhlRzWDXzdsN5IEg7ILK_EQ56zA9jcQ-fPPr3cS5cgV1YVlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Copa (cup) of disappointment…

Picking up something in the Poco area and was deciding on some Korean food or this place. In the end, decided on this place since it’s been decade or longer since I have been to this place.

Upon entering, it seems like the interior went through a bit of change and renovation. The place was pretty empty except for 3 booths seated with customers, maybe it was near closing time (1.5hrs before closing). Everything appeared to be clean throughout the restaurant with a comfortable spacing between the tables and booths.

The service was subpar from the server, maybe she was more focused on cleaning and getting off work. When the owner/ manager took over, it was a lot better and she was more polite.

Here were the food I ordered;

1. Sizzling Hot plate combo B+B (chicken steak & sausages) with borscht soup, spaghetti , cold lemon tea. The chicken was a little dry and the soup was a bit off and warm only. And the hot plate didn’t sizzle at all, maybe a 3 second frisk sound?
2. Sizzling hot place combo A+B (filet mignon & deep fried oysters) with lobster bisque, steamed rice, add lobster tail $23 extra. The filet mignon was horrible, first time ever struggling to chew a filet mignon, it was dry and didn’t taste fresh. The oysters were little midgets. The steamed rice was more like overnight rice just added a bit of water and a quick heat up by the microwave, it was dry and hard. And lastly the lobster tail was horrible; it had that bad fishy taste to it, one tiny bite from that and had to stop cause not worth food poisoning myself from it. And once again the sizzling plate wasn’t even warm!! (Facepalm) The only thing okay was the lobster bisque.

Overall, I was quite disappointed with the food. I don’t remember it being this bad? What happened? Closer to closing time and whoever the cook in the kitchen was didn’t give 2 cents about the food being served? Is it really that hard to hire a decent cook nowadays after the pandemic? And for crying out loud, it only takes 30 seconds to heat up the iron plates and how can one pawn off such a bad bowl of rice in a Chinese restaurant? I honestly would send this cook packing for retirement if working for me, definitely wouldn’t tolerate this kind of bs jeopardizing my business.

I guess I retained my good nature and composure by taking into consideration that the owner/manager was very polite and friendly; very poise and elegant with the services. I guess that’s the only good part of this experience and kept my positivity inlined. Just enjoyed a quick instant noodle when back home lol","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMMcEYpyZUuanHEcQL55fa0WprgsuAX0S3V4h87&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-1-25"},{"Name":"Chang Wun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXinnRETbtdmwq0G3dzHpocXq4c0y1kT8tCLTmXT5-MPrsCx3WH9g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went back for the breakfast. There are a lots of people in the breakfast timing, the breakfast set is cost effective! Will revisit!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPglBpXDu8S3-D1K1Vx9zNGj1s7HzGBk70B8aKE&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2024-1-4"},{"Name":"Angie L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKwNm9A8ohrfnu_XFwYhP8N-ACXPuzjT8lHAp_d40ZyvMetcg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is Hong Kong style fusion restaurant. The selection is quite good for anything from appetizers, steak and fries, to noodles, rice, soup, combos and beverages.

There's Western style combo that comes with soup, main and drink & Asian style combo comes with Chinese soup, main and rice, no drink. You may think the price is on the high side but you won't disappoint by the portion.

Service is not bad but when is not busy. They are not dial in.

They charge $0.50 per take out container that I have no complaint to support the environmental recycling.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDjOVajotJjtkKeh90GhichQoqjYaMOeW4VKP9&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2022-1-2"},{"Name":"Nathan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6aOctokU9KmE5fwo6-6THfOky0imQyJSKP9b0jCAM3iXNSZtK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Low price, good food. What more can I say? I love Hong Kong food. Copa Cafe has good service, the waiters are attentive, friendly, and efficient.

One time, we came here late at night and they still received us and were patient despite us staying beyond their closing time. I’ll always remember the staff’s patience and hospitality.

As you can tell, I really like their noodles 😂🍜","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmD0avsIDuv7S0oR3k1m2RCOwZwtXixWPr-ed3&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2022-12-15"},{"Name":"Bespoke Happier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_JY_sOUqfgLP_sU_CBSIZzGgEmarbG08tg34uKbeN8ljU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Copa Cafe, a popular Hong Kong-style restaurant in Vancouver, is a hidden gem that I frequent when I'm in the mood for a hearty meal. Although there are only two other Hong Kong-style restaurants in Coquitlam, I prefer Copa Cafe for its extensive menu options and exceptional service compared to its competitors. If you become a member, which costs $15 per year, you can enjoy a 10% discount on all orders, which is a great deal.

One of the highlights of Copa Cafe is their breakfast menu, which boasts generous portions that won't hurt your wallet despite the current high prices. On my recent visit, I opted for the satay beef noodle and shared the cheese, spinach, and bacon omelette with my husband. We also ordered two cups of their famous Hong Kong-style milk tea. After applying the 10% membership discount, our bill was a reasonable $23 with the tip included.

Overall, we were pleased with both the quality and quantity of our breakfast. The flavors were satisfactory, and the portions were generous. Copa Cafe is a must-visit spot for anyone who loves Hong Kong-style cuisine and wants to try something new. The ambiance is cozy, and the service is top-notch, making it an ideal spot for a date or a casual gathering with friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSzLi3djIKGAYOhylqv9qdoGJbTHEE6Sfx7hU&fid=0x0:0xa9d123f17cb34070"],"When":"2023-6-17"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Dahee Sim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUX9xskvqrMlPhfaEjei8fHc2AKp7yd0SfCkRSHV-khbg0nQPk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you’re into Korean food and seafood, you’ve got to check out “Bambada”! The food is super fresh, delicious, and the portions are really generous. I went there for a family gathering, and it was awesome—they’ve got menu options for both adults and kids. The staff were super friendly, and every table has a call button, so you can get service right away. They even prepped and served the lobster for us! The place is pretty spacious too, so it’s perfect if you’re dining with a group. I’m definitely going back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMrT2-09aoOderpUIuvuSh-mnAyWNJrCX3VHSE8&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-12-27"},{"Name":"Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJcSTrvAkETp5GS3z8RhAHVaYouKSaPeknm0ZxbLuelbq-2-0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's a great place to try Korean food in various styles. The seafood is fresh, and the food is delicious. Definitely worth a try. The service is good as well. The only thing to note is that we felt really thirsty after the meal. 😂","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMTZPvyF2Tj-s66US3VDJ-XiHdiAW02TVEMXv5r&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-10-17"},{"Name":"Uucky L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVU-arllP44rVa-XSyXWrd0b-hNq7ECu4284KMlWJ8XxeidF78qg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food taste needs improvement.

Don’t come if you can’t eat spicy at all.
I ordered Beef tartar bibimbap, seafood on rice. Both of them comes with a red sauce, claimed to be non-spicy, but they are actually a little-little spicy.

The beef in Beef tartar bibimbap has some tendon (?) in it, not as soft as I think, so you need to chew a bit more than just swallow it.

Seafood on rice, even added the red sauce, is kinda bland. The rice is a pretty wet/sticky.

Fried oyster & fries only have 5 pieces of oysters.

The server is kind and nice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOD199c5zDxdMM7Ds_dRLkXLpgJnCeuNirilncm&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"C L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWFSCt_t74XiqlEdz6jDYOHmtwc4pgb3Fve6nsF3wEBwwz9hl0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was my first time dining at this restaurant after a strong recommendation from friends who live in the neighbourhood. The experience and food did not disappoint! We held a birthday party for 13 people, which was tricky for the layout of the tables. However, the staff were beyond accommodating and made it work. They could have used a few more servers on a busy Saturday night, but the staff were very friendly and immediately responsive whenever we asked.

We ordered a variety of dishes, including the seafood hot pot, fishcake soup and fried fish. Amazing flavours and textures, with generous portions that are ample for sharing! The fried items were light & crispy. The steaming umami soups had just the right amount of spicy kick. You won't find traditional bibimbap, japchae or pancakes because their menu heavily features innovative takes on fresh seafood - not for those with shellfish allergies! Plenty of Korean spirits to test out & quench your thirst! At first glance the prices seem high but considering that the plates can be shared, the restaurant offers great value. Will definitely be returning to try the other menu items!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7rbCmBk0xQzNEDNpQI0kMl_DuMnV3myDZBA-X&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"Hyebin Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUjDtbZAwmClVNZWe8in7iKPeuWFpJk3xV63n3oUYqAkU_8FufJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had seafood ttukbaegi and clam bibimbap a few weeks ago. It was a good combination with the soup and the bibimbap. Not that spicy and had perfect level of spiciness for both.
The restaurant was cozy with booths and looked good for having meal + drinking.
The service was also good. I enjoyed their tea comes with a tea pot. I will definitely visit again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPAW_pwiNbZD2uo1clqF1wwWNE4bFs3c-7MXZAm&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"Kwang s Koo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJFo3VGQh4dEQHrPSivYNI5XIEy1BykoaCVmEDpxsBAeHTAFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"From entering to getting our food…was about 1 hour…

The small seafood hotpot…was 90% clams and mussels…maybe 3-4 prawns couple of abalone and a few other things…I do wish there was less clams and mussels…and has some kind of fish…","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzs80B65n9dqKlhGLZj9jkiEpWUFk5mHNnEtfR&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Toshiyuki Enzo Shirosaki","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUD_24CqvwnpZ272t1lMbFqdPq5Yicn0-6hmHLPLDbUePqw_ASerw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had dinner at a Korean resto bambad the seafood plate was a huge portion for us four people. I like their beef tartare, very soft and tasty.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTthRBMCpezgjbQIAqo9FQZcioh045Rh5XizB7&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-8-12"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I came away from the restaurant with a great first impression. The food was solid, especially for the price, and the customer service was decent.

I highly recommend that you get their signature steamed seafood pot. We got a small and it was enough for the family of four. They really pack in a ton of high quality seafood in the small pot. The broth at the end is almost like a bonus and it's absolutely killer if you pair it with a shot of soju.

We also got the Korean beef tartar and they give a lot of extra things to eat with the beef like wasabi, and seaweed.

I will definitely be coming back with a designated driver next time so that I can drink.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_ntt397jhPBf8nD0ABEKZBcIgPksxdsnfOV5G&fid=0x0:0x29bff5d1e27f9b5e"],"When":"2024-1-23"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Lyndsay Krause","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUw_d91QaVdyXJ_iD_9n4lPuhHR3K42K7S3ljCJwkny1L-l3IuysA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Mixed feelings on this one.  We went during happy hour for a friend's birthday as a table of four.  Even at the peak during our visit, the restaurant was at max, half full, but they did have a large reservation table of about twenty.  The food was good, but the service was SLOW.
They were clearly short-staffed, as the manager was working behind the bar while we were there, but we had to ask other servers to find our waitress twice and went up to the bar once to order our drinks because we had been waiting for so long.  That being said, they apologized profusely and comped us free desserts and did explain that they were short staffed. However, if you're offering a happy hour with one dollar oysters in a nice, reputable restaurant, then you should be prepared.
We ordered both off the happy hour menu and the regular menu and there was small tweaks. We would have made to each dish, but overall, a pretty satisfying meal.
We will give them another shot to see if the slow service was a one off.
If you park in the underground and register you license plate at the hotel desk, parking is free.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzq5Fru9vEfYxmcJR5xpopeyv6MziJcBBPsKfk&fid=0x0:0xcea729f7201067c9"],"When":"2024-10-29"},{"Name":"Olivia Ng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUIR4XKe445qsIhcDQSa4vWiOM9DrqY3ui4NVU5_YRxUleaadGk6w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I celebrated my husband's birthday at this restaurant during happy hour.
