[{"Name":"Chinonso Obeta","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0yfV5kjQ-Xq9KAUs_4HZeSU_qZxQQ-j4kdZVPxgkKv14HMtX3qg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The doughnuts are so awesome. I would recommend the lemon meringue doughnut for a more savory taste.

The team is so kind and so wonderful. Whenever we come, we love talking to them. And sometimes they even give samples! I’m from Vancouver and I would make the journey any day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOnD07tbCog4k6Z7_LCOaA79-k5AxP773sTP6W&fid=0x0:0xfe2868f806edf31d"],"When":"2024-8-31"},{"Name":"Tyler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5pgqDcV4jXxCDs44gFpKqBE7-kpDe9pqH0qySpykt9h70rZWn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If heaven had a breakfast club, Doughnut Love in Coquitlam would be the founding member. Let me tell you, this place knows how to make your taste buds do the cha-cha. I waddled in expecting a quick sugar rush and left with a full-on breakfast love affair. Here’s the scoop:

First off, the chocolate chip cookie dough doughnut. It’s like someone took my childhood dreams of sneaking cookie dough out of the fridge and deep-fried them into a perfectly golden doughnut. Absolute perfection. Then there was the apple crumble doughnut—crispy, sweet, with that lovely crumbly topping that made me think of Grandma’s kitchen (if Grandma was a Michelin-star chef in disguise). Together, they were like the dynamic duo of dessert—Batman and Robin, but covered in sugar and far tastier.

Now, let me talk about the cheesy smoky breakfast sandwich. My friends, I have had a lot of breakfast sandwiches in my day. I’ve been around the eggy block, had my share of bacon-stacked bagels, and yes, even tangoed with the occasional McMuffin. But this one? It was life-altering. Like, call-your-mom-and-tell-her-you-found-the-one kind of good. I’m not even joking when I say this was the best breakfast sandwich I’ve ever had. Hands down, no debate. The cheese was melty, the smokiness was spot on, and the bread hugged the filling like it knew I needed that kind of emotional support that morning. Bravo, Doughnut Love, bravo.

And then there was the pistachio latte. I thought it was pretty good—creamy with that distinct pistachio nuttiness. But my girlfriend? She took one sip, wrinkled her nose, and gave me that look like I had just offered her a cup of blended brussels sprouts. So yeah, it’s a bit of a polarizing beverage. I was happy, she wasn’t, and I ended up with two lattes. Win-win for me, honestly.

Overall, Doughnut Love is definitely worth the visit. Whether you’re after doughnuts that’ll make you reconsider what you know about dessert or a breakfast sandwich that might just change your life, this is the spot. Plus, it’s always fun to take your taste buds on an adventure—even if it means having to finish your partner’s drink. Check it out. Trust me, your stomach will thank you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNBicJQNVZ3eHQ0mQVOJAQIJgDpPzUg6SHE_QzI&fid=0x0:0xfe2868f806edf31d"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"Sunny Bui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKMzWAiXdng0rCtZP9l45dHvlvYqeLHGoUweyd_OjqtW7kL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing Donut Place! Service was GREAT! The vibe was enjoyable!

HUGE SELECTION! Gluten free, vegan, regular donuts and some that are definitely out of the ordinary.

We’ve been here a few times for these delicacies and have ordered batches for catering. These guys DO NOT DISAPPOINT! They are delicious and have something for everyone (and their diet).

Their staff always greets us with a smile, are considerate with handling of the donuts and make sure we are in and out/got what we need. The inside is very cozy too if you decide to stay a bit!

Great work!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtvlbuizmioa0vN8NfQOqkDtC3FpnlSyy1DFQ&fid=0x0:0xfe2868f806edf31d"],"When":"2024-1-11"},{"Name":"Maria M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmuhUB-INQ3XCbE2M9HT-MdzILSuqxW6ls6tLvy0JgUoxl1f3wCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’m not a donuts person but I sure love hot chocolate. I tried the Tiramisu edition for the hot chocolate festival and it was sensational, it came with a mini tiramisu dessert that also tasted very rich. My husband tried the Mexican special and he liked it but I didn’t dig it hehe, don’t like spicy drinks. His came with churros which were very yummy. Nice spot, lovely service :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXKqm4O7z3Xnll-ng94h2kwwU17u1W4jXTh2U_&fid=0x0:0xfe2868f806edf31d"],"When":"2024-1-24"},{"Name":"Ayesha S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIRN1jDxm-GbV9f53B-tJsf5liCDSU1wXPfJ8zXkEZajwAAmKs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down the best so it’s I’ve ever had! My entire family agrees. I’ve had many donuts but the flavours here are phenomenal. The donuts aren’t overly sweet which I appreciate. Crispy on the outside but soft on the inside! 100/10!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sogolika","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVUzHybtFBRJfBv53jgPRRojyPQpndAKmXiSDkdl1E8GHCzNky1=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was my first time going there and really loved it.
The doughnuts are amazing and also the staff are so friendly,even they gave me a free bag of doughnuts as a gift.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOHmieBrgmprydw9odbYU76hAb1iTyxWuyDjIGc&fid=0x0:0xfe2868f806edf31d"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"Ads","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwDyuvQtXP_VygmU1rNXhUJ0mc48E4h1QtDkdEfrlXmuS-mYhL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Vegan donut haven! These beautiful light and fluffy rings of insanely yummy dough are one of the best in Coquitlam I have tasted and the perfect Friday treat to combo with your morning cup of Joe! Nicely dense with a light and uplifting texture, nicely moist and flawless
Super tasty, excellent bold and quirky, edgy flavors with zero animal-based ingredients.
These were a solid four, however a tad dry and stale and I imagine the fresh morning batch in the morning is legit phenomenal .Writing this review has already sent me into another dough-dream.
I really want to try The Homer (my favorite ultimate donut flavor of all time) and will give this a whirl if I manage to get there at a good time.
Support local businesses!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPfcdDUDpiuADd3RnOCt_7OIHsckDzcPTScbc6Z&fid=0x0:0xfe2868f806edf31d"],"When":"2023-10-27"},{"Name":"Jess Golden","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKNdoWBo5RTPsLB2umQOAwhHEXhhe_ZCgHopw1C7RPs6Tys=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down my favourite doughnut shop, so when my now husband and I eloped yesterday with just a couple friends, I ordered doughnuts for brunch on the big day!  I requested they put our initials on two of them and they threw those extra 2 doughnuts in for free!  They were such a hit and looked so cute plated with chocolate-dipped strawberries. Great value! I also loved the spicy fries. So tasty they didn't even need ketchup!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOupzXR9Znz2moILexerkTwqsTjirx2aPiO1shv&fid=0x0:0x16abda2984fa5eca"],"When":"2024-8-31"},{"Name":"Roozegar Mohammadi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrQru4VExe7pdnc_LNPc1yA4v-RaJaPJWbL5u-B9MOm7dojm-4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"1- Thank you and a quick question  regarding your meat shop,  Is there any Halal certification accredited by Halal Canada?
2- Your answer: "Response from the owner
Thank you for your inquiry! We’re proud to share that our supplier is one of the best Halal meat providers in the entire country, ensuring the highest quality and adherence to Halal standards.
Regarding your question, yes, our supplier is accredited by Halal Canada, so you can shop with confidence.
By the way, if you’ve enjoyed our services, would you consider giving us a 5-star review instead of 3? Your support means a lot to us, and we’d love to hear what more we can do to earn that extra star from you!"

3- my reply to your reply:"Thank you for your reply. Unfortunately, i have to change the mark to 1 star because of the following objective evidences:
"Although you mentioned that your supplier has an accredited halal certificate, based on my observations during everyday shopping and watching your Deli and Meatshop employees, it seems that you are not adhering to halal provider rules. Specifically, you are selling halal and non-halal meat together and using the same knives and surfaces to cut them. The regulations in this regard are similar to those for allergen and non-allergen items, where cross-contamination is strictly prohibited. Rather than this, open packages of halal and non-halal meat inside the freezer or fridge should be completely separated. I recommend that you read the Halal International Standard requirements for retail stores. Until you are able to meet these standards, please remove all halal signage from your store, as it is misleading to Muslim customers in this regard"","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ali Fasihizadeh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXeEgxRiuCQGGcgBhaC0R0-E7HN9SKaiGfOrL8NTnYlp6WMk2xa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently ordered a birthday cake to Suzan at the bakery and I couldn’t be happier with the result! She made the cake even better than the picture I provided, and the taste was absolutely wonderful. Suzan’s attention to detail and skill are truly impressive. I 100% recommend her to anyone who needs a cake for any occasion. Thank you, Suzan, for making our celebration extra special!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkLGVEJkX7JSqcjBAtyVWyK982WANxb6oPss2F&fid=0x0:0x16abda2984fa5eca"],"When":"2024-12-10"},{"Name":"TNME GROUP","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJqpJf_GmiTs4CToZS-fMCCnxdoqhY1CpAyRnezSuViSn0N0w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had an amazing experience with Urban Gate in Coquitlam! I needed a mocha cake last minute, and Miss Susan came through with a beautiful creation that exceeded my expectations. The cake looked fantastic and tasted even better—rich, flavorful, and a huge hit with everyone. I was so impressed by how quickly they handled my request without sacrificing quality. A big thank you to Miss Susan and the whole team for their exceptional service. I’ll definitely be coming back for more!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mehran bakhtiari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX52_I8QBEvpbwP2DsvccLDQ1hUjTB0qEjwNL_660Q7Wjozcaqk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been coming here for lunch several times, they have great food at a reasonable price that you can't find anywhere else in Vancouver. Special thanks to Ms. Afsane, who always provides excellent service.
Ms. Afsane is a professional barista and her coffees are wonderful ❤️👌🏻","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO1xMqJRElD_1t8Z-23lkvD_JcHAGaeFjua0Wpn&fid=0x0:0x16abda2984fa5eca"],"When":"2024-6-3"},{"Name":"meow meow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKrJ-mhNYyKJeNAeH6NNi0zZynSPeNyTmmob3-hI4azgkbLWA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is always delicious and price is always good! We had a server named Sareh who is very friendly and attentive. She’s also recommended and offered sampling authentic food we’ve never tried before and they taste really good and we all love it! It’sone of the best places to have really good quality food and customer service. In addition the atmosphere is very comfortable and inviting.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Fuzzley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuQBLG7TksG6wDxiaXxGD7Hm142h_aQxwM9_mE25IYjf3jo0BguA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"As a long-term customer I was very disappointed with my recent experience at Urban Gate. I brought to the attention of the cashier that I had purchased some barbari bread a few days ago, and that I was told these were baked the night before.
Unfortunately when I took the bread home and opened it on the same day, I found both to be rotten and stale. I did not want to drive all the way back for a little refund that. The following week while shopping at the store, I informed the cashier. All I sought was a simple acknowledgment of my concern and an apology for the inconvenience. Instead, what followed was a lengthy justification about how fresh bread can spoil overnight due to moisture. Additionally, the cashier explained their return policy, stating that I should have brought back the receipt and the rotten bread for a refund.
I felt that the response lacked empathy and a proper understanding of customer service. The interaction came off as arrogant, and it left me feeling undervalued as a customer. It is disappointing to know that, as a loyal customer, my concerns were not taken seriously. I hope Urban Gate can improve its customer service training to better handle situations like this in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marjan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJi5kZ8SK7DmiaOMIRuV-4Ttne1NBXp-Dh_P2EIrXoD-QM7Hw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This store has a good selection of products from my home country , especially in the meat department, where the staff are polite and helpful.
However, the customer service at checkout is very disappointing and rude, especially from the cashier ladies. They rarely greet  and often have a negative attitude. For example, one cashier today threw the receipt on the counter, slammed her hand on it, and walked away without saying anything. I even said hello and thank you, but she didn’t respond. When I asked the others if they had the same experience, they said they did.
These interactions make shopping feel unwelcoming. I hope the staff realizes that everyone deserves respect and that good service is important.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Ping D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-_KBk5-yIGzGmKAkX1L-6QPRrz_RZKkgRnIY4il5exhoL_sw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was a perfect lunch. Kids menu pizza was the same size as the regular pizza. Food and service were both very good. I’d suggest they offer more selections of pizza flavours at lunch time. It’s definitely a good deal to go at lunch. The comfortable meal started with complimentary dinner rolls with garlic oil.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN47_Do9ZdDwPr-MU16mYYSZu6ND1uoZmOWqwg4&fid=0x0:0xcb392bf507fb5484"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"Amanda Green","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWX2-QkU6r0X4DLM6-w27hOoQabXaFOXnHBh92gU3KWWKAd6KWGjA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have ordered takeout before and loved it, so we decided to dine in this time. Very cozy atmosphere and lovely service. The food was so, so fresh and the flavours were outstanding. I ordered the Scusa Mi Pomodoro and I understand now why it's a challenge winner - it was to die for, and I can't remember the last time I had such good, fresh, perfectly cooked prawns. Will definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0E5mjnxKtwgfWXwsftGkVtde8Fcyw_qHRefWm&fid=0x0:0xcb392bf507fb5484"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Jessameen Dela Peña","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9mRpmL8-ZJUG7UPFcnsjzRdxjABif-MswbO1rxgJyyWfns8Jd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a wonderful family dinner at this restaurant! The ambiance is truly lovely, creating a warm and inviting atmosphere. The staff went above and beyond, being both accommodating and welcoming throughout our meal. We highly recommend the Baked Chicken Parmesan—it was absolutely delicious! A great experience all around!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMC3AKdGWBqxc-jukm25cD5f_HXE9kVmRakX-oM&fid=0x0:0xcb392bf507fb5484"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"Nathan Ferlan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUBBwm7N9m9VsEZe8oXWT3QVjEQHlJhduQ22vfMGOziLtc2Ouo=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A Culinary Experience to Remember!

⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️

If you’re looking for a dining experience that leaves you craving more, look no further. I recently had the pleasure of indulging in the most exquisite Pasta & Prawns, and I’m still savoring every memory of it. Each bite was a masterpiece—perfectly cooked pasta with tender, flavorful prawns, all bathed in a rich, savory sauce that danced on my palate. The balance of flavors was simply divine, making it one of the best dishes I’ve ever had.

But what truly made the night unforgettable was the outstanding service. From the moment we arrived, the staff made us feel like we were more than just customers—they made us feel like family. Our server was down-to-earth, warm, and attentive in a way that made the whole evening feel special. Every request was met with a genuine smile and care that is rare to find.

The ambiance, the incredible food, and the impeccable service all came together to create a perfect dining experience. I had such a great time, and I’m already counting down the days until my next visit. Highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6ocpt4jzjfqUqjB2OE7Fa55VrOmI8L5U_KNDR&fid=0x0:0xcb392bf507fb5484"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"James Mendonca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKDOYVs1G-8iT9QF6Fj3_nUauDo1DS6zISrEp3lZ9wij4inDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pasta Polo is an exceptionally great Italian restaurant that serves quality food. You know the workers take pride in their food and service when they post the restaurant's review articles on the walls.

I ordered the Osso Bucco with the Virgin Purple Sour drink. I was served complimentary bread with my entrée that included butter and a bottle of fermented garlic. The bread tasted pretty great on its own while the garlic made it taste much better. The Osso Bucco was delicious with the Bolognese sauce. The side pesto pasta was very good and was well seasoned with parmesan. The non-alcoholic Purple Sour tasted excellent with its exceedingly sweet flavours.

The servers were very formal with their customers when it comes to preparing their tables. They check on me as often as possible during busy hours while maintaining a positive attitude. The establishment was dark yet classy and clean.

I look forward to eating as this restaurant again to try their other entrees.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXlV9QLG73dgmJm2MgWDAp3IaT80Wb7UqKSEgR&fid=0x0:0xcb392bf507fb5484"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"S Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDCpcHtfixdQ1nlZ-cnjxErMYcSiJY3vif9B2kRQjg0W11mPsG=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It’s been a few months since we were here last. We ordered the chicken Marsala and gnocchi.  Both were delicious!  I love the Marsala sauce!  My husband enjoyed the garlic oil that was served with a bun.  The bun was ok. Could have been tastier.  I enjoy good bread and this wasn’t anything to write home about.  Service was excellent. We had Thea and she was great!  I also enjoyed their art gallery.  So much talent.  We will definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZaMW99B_vyd2v_54Cdz758FoKxJtAP-r08b85&fid=0x0:0xcb392bf507fb5484"],"When":"2024-12-1"},{"Name":"Y Man","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUB62F2-VitrTkpd3TexeBmDt6LJ-Ec6lzQvbbyCIp7HJAIiB3b=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lovely Italian restaurant. The carbonara was tasty and creamy,  pasta is fresh and the sauce was enough to cover all the pasta and not drenched in it.  The meatballs were tender and mixed with fresh herbs,  a perfect meat side to the pasta.  The tiramisu was delicious,  creamy melts in your mouth.  Definitely coming back to try other dishes","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdg_N9cATCFpMd2RK_yR7Qj4KSOp6mP1XOgxD7&fid=0x0:0xcb392bf507fb5484"],"When":"2024-9-20"},{"Name":"Marnie Eudela-Umlas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXg_gVRD_Hd9V3XIUh6_P71KHCryea9xsHYGqrZHTuXW_jdxEU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Spent our Mother’s Day celebration in this restaurant and we had a great time. Everything was awesome from food to their service. Our server even took our photos, too bad I forgot his name. The pizzas were all soo good and my fave was the Anchovy pizza. Pastas were yummy and their desserts too were all a treat. We will surely be back :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbGw58cAzM4X4wXEw-LloHV5v2YTXfNlioydQo&fid=0x0:0xcb392bf507fb5484"],"When":"2024-7-2"}]

[{"Name":"Jennifer Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFO0fgPBTIA1yxL3IXSghRJ6EmshLC1YB1a72b-xeg3kpjHx0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a great find! We loved the view of the ocean, the tea was devine, and food was yummy. They make their own sourdough bread as well. We liked our tea so much we bought a bag to enjoy at home. The drive was fun and we felt like we were far from the busy city. I look forward to visiting again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZxwjvX0-_n5Rw5TG4lMSWVZcFPreeqJFIEDBs&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2023-11-26"},{"Name":"Randy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUSb09if5u7GFHKGhGpQrqg8HJqBQmEd3IDfG068mgp2Ghgte_T=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Booked a boat ride up to Indian arm for the Christmas tea festival. The spot was beautifully decorated. The hospitality was great  information on all the teas we sampled was very informative. It was a great night for a boat ride. We thoroughly enjoyed our whole evening there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNQ0PN6AkM3zQ4jMdx90HeKNMpjssL8_HNhnI2D&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2023-11-29"},{"Name":"Hanah Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWsf0-pXkdSTqGJecZlxwp3Bbml3NhidicNq-zEzWIQ7fexEd8QYg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's unbelievable that their fabulous afternoon tea towel was not just tasty but made with quality organic ingredients! Tha fantastic nature scene over the glass wall is a huge plus!
It was a great discover for our family trip in Vancouver trip this year and we will definitely visit again to try their quality tea options (and the rest of food menu).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_WM495E_CrwYXdyVTKzLVd2LApPNOALoKqHGH&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2023-4-16"},{"Name":"Jordan Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLFsjfnS-oiBTX7iRzPhMh-PXM_FEBemeI_C6-8CDhB4SzDFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a wonderful experience at 8 Corners! I loved the remote location as it felt like an adventure getting there. It was also very calm and the vibes were chill.

The building is sitting right off the water so there's a great view of the lake and mountains.

The service staff was very welcoming and friendly made me and my partner feel cozy and comfy.

The food was delicious and I liked that it felt homemade and fancy compared to being made elsewhere and shipped in.

All in all, a great experience, would highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWr3Obt5HJqdC_akITzItu4a7HFkDNtbbgkgpw&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2023-6-10"},{"Name":"Scott Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHpW7vGME__Zs4wKjXR04Upnw88bkVVyz-H2288JsHocq9vI3r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They’re only open 2 days a week from 11am to 4pm so make sure that you visit them during that time!

They have authentic green tea imported all the way from South Korea and it clearly shows that they really care about their tea and knows their stuff.

The owner came out multiple times during our time there to ask how we were enjoying the tea and the sandwiches. Do t get me wrong, they can be a bit pricy but I think the whole experience is well worth it.

It takes a bit of an effort to make it out there but it only adds to the charm of the place. I would love to try out their high tea experience next time!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN02qEQo0Hmand3R-ml_1CphZqZtsdy5csJ8XAb&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2022-9-18"},{"Name":"Jihyun Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ6QtUokr8e5CT7oQaQrOHr0gHr2y_Oz1hLcsCumlH7cfOpRg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was looking for a nice afternoon tea place and did some research to find out 8 Corners. Their photos on Google well represent what you’d get from the afternoon tea experience. Id say this is a best hidden gem i found recently. Stunning view, great selection of teas. Well explained finger foods and great staff as well. This place seems that it’d be nice for a wedding. The price for the afternoon tea is reasonable but dont forget you also get the view and inner peace.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNnUGZ9L1l8FJ5k1JcwxQ5IZ8fpqom7N5_35C-K&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2023-7-9"},{"Name":"Terri Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWdHMQamP6ntk6cmD8m9VHj4cLgJWNXVSwfy5Jk1_ks8LpnASP1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Please check their website and READ through everything. This is not your commercial high tea cafe located on a big street. It's literally located deep inside a park and make reservations online. Very unique experience away from the city life. Just the drive alone is an experience. The food was ok though. The atmosphere and surrounding makes it worth it. The building next door seems to be a wedding venue too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNONYUafefHXdt0EAWE1xLMDL_yyi5ZA-70Yrhy&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2022-12-29"},{"Name":"Angela Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVbKkg8N4MGypttPdK2tiQGP6agzZ49zgTH9Ca58X1Et2jkg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Who knew this was hidden inside Belcarra! A very nice surprise. You need to make reservations and pay ahead of time ($65 a person and parties of 2-4). You can also attempt to drop by for their regular menu. We tried a regular set as well as a vegan set. Our favorite parts were the savoury sandwiches on their homemade sourdough bread. We wished that the desserts were more varied - they were heavily matcha/red bean centered and on the less sweet side because of the Korean owned establishment. The teas were great, and service was good as well. The road in isn’t paved, so be aware. The tea room can be a little stuffy since it’s an open kitchen, but it didn’t bother us too much. Overall, the grounds are lovely and it’s a unique experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPd8lODHOm9KVj3JShfBtYR6Og9Z6GwdRo9-s5U&fid=0x0:0xd02c86ecc43edc64"],"When":"2023-12-7"}]

But after 20 years of ordering from this place, the last driver that stopped past year really cheesed me off..  read me loud and clear.. you don't get paid double for delivering to my house.  I paid the $4.99 delivery fee once and I'm not going to pay it a second time.  If you don't like that then don't deliver for this pizza company anymore.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Teresa D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIEpA50cEAUamyww7Ej8yX922Xy8DwbdgYJV39QLILzuQU0ZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We order from this location regularly. The service is usually just ok, but it's close and convenient, and the pizza isn't bad, so we continue to buy from them. Tonight, I picked up our order - 2 pizzas, 2 dips. (We needed to replace our expired jars of dip in the fridge as they were past their due date and had gone off / were runny.) When I got home with our order, I noticed that my husband's dip has a best before date of Jan 31, 2025. My dip, however, is listed as Sept 18, 2024 (so, 3 weeks from now). We are a 2-person household who like different pizzas and different dips / flavours. As with everything, the cost of pizza and dips, etc has gone up. A jar now costs $7.65 (a little less than 1/2 the cost of a small pizza). I can't possibly eat this much dip in 3 weeks time, and am annoyed that my husband's dip will last so much longer than mine. So, when I call to complain, I'm told that \"customer care\" says that the dips only last for two weeks after they've been opened, and that they can't help, compensate or accommodate me in any way because the dip wasn't sold as expired! Unbelievable. What terrible customer service. I'm suddenly much more motivated / inclined to give our money to one of the many other pizza places in Port Moody. Thanks, Panago.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Canucks","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRD017oq3npI5mSw9FYdihSoqGLv78YZJ4GTo_GR01RktMzAtd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Having a very nightmare experience with a gluten allergy with my family and sickness. We got a refund for that order thank you - but somehow another order was placed (not by me) for 91$ and Uber is saying it’s not refundable! Please help and resolve and remedy this. I never placed another order after this and am being scammed out of 91$ for nothing… nothing was made or sent to me last night. I was at work and noticed a charge on my credit card. Thanks for any help! Used to be my go to place…","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"O T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNMZRDyPmCXOIYr2knffcKqnpyxzie7qHVjFWoC2-ZmJX5_do-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"This is my favorite pizza, and I have no complaints about the taste. It's delicious but not healthy, with lots of MSG in it. You know, typical fast food quality, which is what Panago offers. The issue is mainly the store and its cleanliness. If I'm not mistaken, this store is located in a first-world country and in a nice neighborhood. However, I would like the owner to ask himself how clean his store should be. Their washroom is a joke. The soap dispenser nozzle is basically on the sink, and the door hinge is broken and will soon fall on someone's head. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Lina Huine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXTc90UClGdW5-vlLdRudv0nYQ1eUmIsZfcJ8sj-8pxZav3xZGO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A nice restaurant and very welcoming. It was our first time here, and we were ready to try all you can eat!! They had quite a few items in the salad bar. Hot paella, salads, veggies, rice, mashed potato’s and beans. There was lots of choices for the grilled meats, pork, chicken, sausages, chicken hearts and lamb. Although some meats I tried felt a little too rare they were ok, I prefer my steaks medium well. You can ask for certain cuts while they cut the meats for you. They are brought by the server to every table. My favourite was the pork ribs. So much flavour and so tender.  The grilled pineapple with cinnamon was also so delicious. This is the perfect place for meat lovers. The buffet price is $49.00 per adult and you have a 2-hour dining limit.
All Drinks cocktails, beer and wine and are not included with the price per person. Service is efficient our server was quite attentive.  The dining area has a nice open touch and the Samba dancers were lovely! Parking can be hard to find and it’s a tight squeeze . Reservations are recommended.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkJM-iflMuGBgRbrRP5gP9QpmkbJa6mzraUFe9&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-6-29"},{"Name":"Peter Au","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUwBxrbZVtlTM1OV2SDGm3NwMn7yUHEw1MaS3fh_B2utP_W4kON=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my second time coming here. With my family of 4 this time. The salad bar was vastly improved. Good variety. The meat was excellently prepared. The servers were very attentive. Everyone were having a good experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNY1ZKhYQV1ilQvIAxUYreDVvtD35cj39Sf8BQG&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-10-24"},{"Name":"Hassan Makhlouf","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYREoqUkazVJoJhrGCrjS5g1lIMahzFkhsZA1Ir7O3A-YofJyb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time to be there and it was Friday night , the week night of the show.
Staff were friendly and helpful and guided us through how the process work for all you can eat meat.
Salad buffet included some famous Brazilian choices.
Different types of meat come to your table to cut slices if you want. The only thing is that they should provide more well done options, although they bring some when we requested.
Don’t miss their brisket, grilled shrimp and their lamp . They are amazing.
Show reflect Brazilian Samba and it was nice.
Just to know it is for added cost as it appears as a separate item in your bill .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPBj2bT_NRXD8W3R_E0mCSNY-FPlWJIquWOJxEz&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-6-30"},{"Name":"Charles Wang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVnyXkcgy3RAI1654HPbt1rZ6zUisia7pCqDlJbMaDIITSvFO3w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Atmosphere is great! We went in a nice weather afternoon. 4/5
Service is excellent, from servers to bartenders. 5/5
Food is average 2/5. It has a good range but no premium meats.
It has sausage, pork belly, lamb leg, beef flank, beef flank steak, beef strip loin, chicken heart, bacon wrapped chicken, but no premium parts like short ribs or tenderloin. So I would only want to go again if it’s $35 per person. I don’t eat much and I don’t feel it’s cost worthy. It could be great for young adults who eats a lot.
The good part about their food and services is that they would cut the cooked portion off and go back to cook again, measuring the best time.
I enjoy the top sirloin (which I cannot cook so well at home) which is very soft and smooth. Chicken heart is tender and good as well. Another recommendation is flank steak, so tasty.
I normally enjoy strip loin (New York steak) but I don’t like theirs because the center is too chewy and the outside is well done already. They cut such a thick portion and I cannot cut or chew the size they gave me.
Another thing I wouldn’t recommend is the chickens wrapped by bacon, because the chicken breast is dry and flavorless.
Forgot to mention, my wife enjoyed the deep fried banana and pineapple, and she had to order the second basket.

Overall, great place to hangout with friends because they don’t kick people away, you can take your time to enjoy the night; but not very worthy of going with young child because you cannot take your time. It can be ideal for young adults but it can be heavy on stomach for some people.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO71AVG9xBwG2lHo8QZdN5fg_LmksBW0S3Fg_cp&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-8-5"},{"Name":"Patrik Balian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkRyDf2r0GCbtZlv3fAL2_00qnr8ZzvdLDimiVoG484QU7TX1agw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Steaks! BBQ! Chicken! Tasty Salads! Oh so fresh oh so good place for birthday's and celebrations 🍾 ✨️ 😍 💕 The culture is alive at RIO BBQ! The staff were super helpful and friendly. The value on the drink variety alone was very exotic.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfqY43TYpGYjPwCt12r_wzhCPFfbtGR57abtzP&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-10-2"},{"Name":"Bernie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPXTBFQGy4UZogf6r0hGxUGZ8fvtwePPN5iicbAtQksaWtpwOP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Festive and welcoming restaurant ambiance. As a first-timer, curiosity brings me from their ads.  It’s an amazing dining experience to enjoy an ‘Eat All You Can’ of side dishes and sizzling meat on parade brought by the server at every table. Steaks, chicken, lamb, sausage, liver etc are perfectly roasted and deliciously complemented by a buffet of a whole array of South American starters of seafood paella, salads, rice, beans, soup and a whole lot more.  My favourites are the grilled bacon-wrapped chicken and prime rib steak.  This is the perfect place for meat lovers. The day buffet price of $49/per adult is reasonable for a 2-hour dining limit.

Drinks choices include cocktails, beer and wine and are billed separately. Service is wonderful, servers are efficient and friendly.  The dining area has a nostalgic touch, well-maintained and clean.  Designated parking places are available.  Reservation is a must.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGEwxGO_TrBQEBohiMCpR8Ge6Ct3bHPznCpk6i&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-6-7"},{"Name":"Jo ?","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIH6ejfn1zBGZNLGyX14NChaJTKE5bREgcEhd70QYQAvcdrmO5=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went there on a Friday night! My friend bailed on me, so I’m all by myself.  It’s recommended by my friend, I didn’t  want to cancel.
Seated beside the window, had good view of kitchen door where foods are came out. Variety of meat I tasted : beef with different cuts are roasted to almost perfection, juicy and with  flavor! Roasted pork, sausages, chicken drum stick, shrimps!  Lamb was lacking that special flavor which lamb should have, maybe it was done to please most customers? It’s all you can eat meat with a 2-hr time frame. I saw no one exactly put a timer on you or kick you out when times up😅🤣
Self serve salad bar is great, lots of different ways to fill up a plate to your liking. There’s white rice and a big container of Paella? It was the only disappointing food for the night: was mushy and only few shrimps and mussels. It was very salty too. In contrast to what shown in their website (which was very attractive)!🥲
Kudos to all staff there, always big smiles, helpful, ready to chat if you want and leave you to your food if you prefer👍🏼
Especially great appreciation to the host Daisy, very friendly, full of energy and big smile! Can see that she was on her feet all day but still kept the vibe! 👏👏👏","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEhI2u_fl7DmTCHMgfMIYQlhsa0jA4MF3it6AV&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"Paulo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJLcA_plm7bkWjnqTJrnEsHhDOSAcI0Thh-Pnw_Wtq2KxuMbiQFg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Last time I went to a Brazilian all you can eat steak place was maybe 15 years ago (Samba in Vancouver).

We've seen/passed this place so many times and finally went here for my birthday today with the family.

It was good. Food was delicious, service was amazing, our server (her name was desea?) was lovely and amazing.

No complaints from us. Definitely will come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-rXlJWcW9GXrwGqkZtRBMlKPFmnmqCCpPXvD2&fid=0x0:0x3f2c22e89f43d5bc"],"When":"2024-2-3"}]

[{"Name":"Dayton Thodos","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJV9JY4oOkjLyO9lR45ss9uXXi5Exxer4saXp5_WEPdsdlZMSI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ate here today. Had the chana masala which was very good. Only $9.99 for all their lunch specials until 2 PM which is a really good price. I appreciated the sign in their window and wanted to give them my business. Glad I did. We could use more people caring for our communities. ❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7P_p5bi-KKlj17E6nrpIy_8Qw1DZ6FIr7Gun5&fid=0x0:0x6a0dbb1d99a6ada2"],"When":"2024-5-18"},{"Name":"JR","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK3_YGWEMNJWYNkYPArm1lJ_HP7RyEaBVSqqscwHuICtS_M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolutely garbage "Greek" food, if you can call it that. I can tell whoever is in the kitchen is guessing at what Greek is supposed to taste like and they have no culinary skill at all, none, zip, ziltch. Stop selling this food immediately. It belongs in the trash. Sorry not sorry you shouldn't be selling this, you're ripping people off.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Byron Lin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI1ZIkhKMx6Jhytrhte_ByMuWA-wf7fxdgXGR0uc8XVcrVhDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great middle eastern food at affordable prices.

Got their beef shami lunch special with a mango lassi for $15.

Tasted great and good portions. Owners were nice as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOhcQk43-JRrjVLW-AoompYCS-XyyjI2JjL3NO3&fid=0x0:0x6a0dbb1d99a6ada2"],"When":"2023-12-27"},{"Name":"v","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMalQNO5O3WgU0LxOYrpn0-JYQ9ou7NIB8ukVrbj1B_A3Hleze=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Sorry.......not great. We ordered the butter chicken and naan. The butter chicken had the consistency of tomato soup and frankly the flavour to match. Way to runny. I will say the actual chicken in the dish was nice, not too dry, but they hardly give you any. The naan was a bit on the chewy side. We are going to stick with our old faithful which is strictly Indian food. This place may offer too many styles of food which may mean they are just mediocre making all of them instead of being fantastic with one style. We don't recommend nor will we be ordering anything from them in the future... even though we only had the Indian since it was mediocre we are going to have to assume the rest is as well. I almost forgot... we ordered a piece of cheesecake as well..it was horrible, I actual think it had gone off and they smothered it with all this sweet sauce to cover it up. DISGUSTING. I hope we don't end up sick from the few bites we had before we realized there was something up. If I could give this place zero stars I would.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMnBSkxO-LuBP1CDOgiqV7Ke19lsi_tq2kPrRFW&fid=0x0:0x6a0dbb1d99a6ada2"],"When":"2021-8-9"},{"Name":"Jonathon Gagnon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJWthbVfHKE36MOK846jxUfBzBByHNknTZyAsz0C7lTAOrW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolute trash. $30 lamb roast mostly fat. Hard potatoes Rude staff member when I called. We have much better options in the tri cities. Embarrassingly bad","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOtEEdC0q3sBBCsuthy7Z5uI-yPybnLqY8uC4&fid=0x0:0x6a0dbb1d99a6ada2"],"When":"2024-4-24"},{"Name":"Rachel L Ballard","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWr-srklsKskWjS7X9-4AIJrZem2BuSI0cPQTV50FmTOQvnByZ_=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Calimari meal was awful, only ate it because I ordered through Door Dash and was hungry. Greek salad had no dressing and was half full of white onion. Nothing on the plate tasted like Greek food. Maybe they do other cuisines better, but I would never order Greek from this place at all. Wish I could get my money back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8BlmH2-mClq09VJ4q5kh6UailoOk9lZYvwcel&fid=0x0:0x6a0dbb1d99a6ada2"],"When":"2023-6-14"},{"Name":"Liam Moss","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWZPZS67TQqx3Uea76ERA7BRjgSHA5yKUONJDHUOaBBanw5cV7a9w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Their curry’s are unbelievable, as a Brit living in Canada I really miss good curry. The Pakistanis and Bangladeshis who run our Indian restaurants in the UK do a great job. The Indians who run the Indian restaurants here do a terrible job both in value and quality. Forgive me if I’m wrong but I believe these guys are Afghan, who have far more in common culinary wise with Pakistan and hence they make much better curry then Sirdaarjii. Bravo, I can’t wait to come back. Amazing value too with the lunch special, great for a work lunch.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tony Cima","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU7L4JEMxZTTSVa9798NKuFVKr18jcX25PgN9UVVk9MTGHQaVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hidden gem for Middle Eastern and Indian food in Coquitlam.  Delicious food, very reasonably priced, with kind, caring staff.  Highly recommended!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"A.J. Canadian","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU0mITu_1OR_MuXzhVIkPjHjZnimy2Y-mI64r72OA1Zbucah6-N=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I usually enjoy my visits to Mariner Brewery in Coquitlam. They offer good tasting craft beer and food. Comfortable seating with TV screens playing sports. Patio seating as well. Free parking lot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZOep9PY3X_UZZI0gHiWKfkD3_Rwg7S6IlxOXy&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-12-2"},{"Name":"shotavi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNMh1hfEFIJYaCTSLthIdHQ3TANUnSyqWujpD58h8MinLMJyw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was looking for a casual place to grab a drink and found this spot on Google Maps.

The atmosphere was really nice and relaxing, and I thought it would be great to come here on a sunny day.

This time, I only ordered a drink without food, but next time I want to come back for some food and beer.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8MebbW-WnQTRvvxKA_I0ZvOyBNH4FxfomcuPu&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-9-18"},{"Name":"jasonbenj","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXesObwVr-MYoNivn747YIQhYO4b8Vn-9xP5t36MuM6wxR0MRI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"First time back since the renovation. Sadly, it looks like a lot of re-branding of the same old product is 90% of it. Also, they took all the good items off the menu. RIP beer cheese dip, you will be missed. Sorry to say but it's not for me anymore. Also, $13 25 flight before tax !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOql9qRevUlia8U9C-dRW3PT6r5a5AmKlZ5qwHk&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"Marisa Lenarduzzi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIbCzpGYeIKBI2SunoaFci_IoZvVVnbxBDnsfb3PLewJQAy3A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great beers and great food for a brewery as well. We got the fries with mango chipotle and it was delicious! There’s also a great atmosphere inside - not too loud, good lighting and very clean. Would go again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7VsLepap0KHEDl1zc5eEsDCQ9ndL4l7M2shto&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-10-12"},{"Name":"Christina Faminoff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX12CPz5calL7TtQ0KnMyeMWTusgq3nB56xjWsl60LKS9agnIFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just had the burger of the month, the Fall Forage smash with the falafel patty, and a stout. Both were awesome. Falafel was super fresh and tasty. I've tried most of their beers, and kombucha, and I appreciate that they are all really different, and don't all just taste like hops. Love that they added a food menu! Nice to be able to get good hot food instead of just snacks, like a lot of breweries. This is one of my favourite places. Would recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNi9KQYgc3UAPTrvyVhcEulEHKDPEevANrCc4rQ&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"May Zhagro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KviWdU_UGm6yjKPv-6aFaljm1EC_ecrxYhnt_LO3duiyBNho=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Came to this brewery with a meetup group and it was an on experience. There were limited non-alcoholic drinks on the menu, but they had four different craft sodas. I tried the cherry cola craft soda, the taste was interesting, but it wasn’t great, a bit flat. I also tried the pretzel and they were very generous with the mustard, but it was overall still very bland and got too cold too quickly. It’s a nice space to hang out and it can get busy even on weekday evenings.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5hAZODlvyOhf9B5lJi8jBxhRFGkFm5uo_rePD&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2023-12-21"},{"Name":"Lauren St John","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWi3pWsd_jh8y8V1Pl7XbMiNRgCVHq-YYCdAOx_KkkOFRnXREk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Pass on this one. Unless you're a beer and ale aficionado, keep going. Sorely disappointed in the food. We heard it had improved with new owners but it's obvious that more changes are needed. They charge $17 (plus tax and tip) for 8 chicken wings. That's outrageous. We tried the Jamaican patties and they were ok. The venue is cozy with more outside seating than inside. The service is "meh." The beer was average. There's not a lot for non-alcoholic beverages. The whole experience left us nonplussed. We will not go back or recommend it.  We spent $65 for 2 beers, 8 wings, a can of ginger ale and 2 Jamaican patties. And the pressure to tip 20% even though there's no table service, left us perplexed!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM_Ekb1Paet7mkMRPuwFGpkIuDRB9sqyDH14sUc&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2023-9-8"},{"Name":"E. C Arteaga G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxwN6PAknbpzp4-FRd4QkWYRhq1QUPT2iG2_oEOzRgEc5F0GVH1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I was waiting for the perfect opportunity to go try this local brewery and today was the day. We were greeted by our server who was kind and knowledgeable about their beers.  They recommended the Blonde Ale ( Low Gravity Mango) super delicious. But, the food was not what we expected. The fries tasted bland and raw. It tasted like everything was made in an air fryer. The sliders we had were bland and the buns were not toasted. The chicken wings were a hit and miss. Some where nice and fell off the bone and others where hard as a rock. I would definitely try this place again because the beer is their saving grace but I will double think about ordering food again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPN8xjotriAojNGVe5wIIRD29aZaMWIHah5pNDd&fid=0x0:0x7a7b14f9a83a2c18"],"When":"2022-3-30"}]

[{"Name":"Yeshvi Mehta","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVHHFZUwt0pnim38TVGVDQUhu3Obi33NtK1Ek9rBbru761t74M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I happened to be in the area, and was craving some thing Indian. Found this place nearby and we chose to dine in.
The service was super quick and kind, even though we were pretty close to last call on a weekday. The interiors are cute & cozy, felt like I was sitting comfortably at home.

The food was also great! We licked our plates clean!! I would totally come back.
We ordered:
- Daal makhani
- malai kofta
- paneer tikka

The only thing I wouldn’t order again is the masala papad, it’s a simple dish and I feel like I’ve had it better and so worth a try here, but not worth ordering again. I could recommend using better quality papad (this tasted like the microwavable ones I buy) and adding cilantro on top!
I can also suggest skipping the rasamalai and gajar ka halwa.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSDjFW06q2OYUYcOeDlM0qXqAsx7PriBcfC29x&fid=0x0:0x35dd030f9f55b602"],"When":"2024-11-15"},{"Name":"Y L.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKV887-1nS5R1_0KzCym2KWUc3U6pndK939JM55kJWey6Ce8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time we tried this place from map search. We ordered Chicken vindaloo and Kadai Paneer and some fish and veggie sidedish. Everything was very tasty, and the curry had lots of stuff inside. Their galric naan was very savory. The service was amazing! Sunday mid afternoon, and most tables were full. Will come back with family.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNOELPHUm52kqW3zDV3koxo5VImAINHyx18l_Jm&fid=0x0:0x35dd030f9f55b602"],"When":"2024-7-21"},{"Name":"Katie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJN3p8cZHE5md15OEErKZKNn97Wi4lfH4nosGtOcXvlYGz2XA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The sauce is delicious but I can definitely tell the chick is not fresh. I really want to like this place. I ordered butter chicken many times but the chicken*always* doesn't taste fresh. It tasted like they used frozen chicken or old chicken. Please make this place better!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"陈晓景","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKGC0re95jO_hDOolePpTdMH_6cWbYDgFuh210eUCCpyMpiSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food is delicious and service is quick and good. Backgroud music volume could be a little lower. Nice a small but clean spot with a beautiful Indian style chandelier.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-JksCwe0tHsc-A7xhUiCTe9CsUtM0Cyc1Kmfg&fid=0x0:0x35dd030f9f55b602"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Linda N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIuD1_pd2ly4vtFhb8M-kjUT3J9JuCYtyHfu9UlF8IRT0IUpuI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cute and cozy Indian restaurant. I absolutely love their food! Their butter chicken is so mouth-watering good. Service was great and staff is extremely friendly. 10/10 recommend and will definitely be coming back for more :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXf8xMYxAiAkIocwrP_DFEwgjR_QP6IvaAPonY&fid=0x0:0x35dd030f9f55b602"],"When":"2023-7-16"},{"Name":"Nat A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnjKr4KNFAObzj2bIvH9BRInxwKsSvEg1PM25bKfvhxtWZTWHoog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is a small restaurant with about 4 tables. It wasn't too busy inside. They were able to put two tables together to accommodate our group of 5 adults and 4 kids. More customers were coming in for pick up.

My favorite dish was the Palak Paneer. The flavor was so good! The honey garlic cauliflower was something different which was also very good. I preferred the Butter Chicken rather than the Butterica. The Butter Chicken had a lot more flavor and spice. My main dish was the Goat Curry. The goat was nice and tender but I found the sauce a little salty. The garlic naan was very fresh tasting and had good flavor.

Overall, many of the dishes were good and the server was friendly and helpful with describing dishes.

I would definitely come back to try more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjVHWe5_Z1UvW7YTHaCkuTZGDbrNMCiP5Dy9-2&fid=0x0:0x35dd030f9f55b602"],"When":"2022-12-23"},{"Name":"wilsonjoshwilson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPoK02al9DYZ9GLC0wDSU4FEAZAAPuuG6qlzOOh_26eyk877fT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Ordered Milaap via UberEats.

I ordered the butter chicken, rice, garlic naan and two samosas.

Let’s start with the samosas..not great. I’ve had a lot of samosas in my day, but unfortunately these are some of the worst.

Tasted like unseasoned potatoes with a slight hint of masala..Very underwhelming.

As for the butter chicken, it had a decent flavour. I ordered hot and the sauce had a good amount of kick. The taste itself was a bit lacking in the depth department, but still satisfied my craving.

Some chicken pieces were a tad dry and it felt like the chicken wasn’t overly seasoned. Again, I ordered via Uber, so the quality could be better if the food didn’t have to travel.

As for the rest of the food, I enjoyed the garlic naan and didn’t have issues with the rice.

If you do end up dining here, I would suggest eating at the establishment for a fresher experience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shefali Sapru Khwaja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURPkwy9A4LfdBYA4JLdXbkGazuimmmuX-ZT5ge4C45KzdYyjHW=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Had a craving for sweet so ordered just desserts which turned out horrible ! The gulab jamun was hard inside , the kulfi was a blob of flavoured ice  and the gajar halwa was not fully cooked ! Not ordering again!","Images":null,"When":""}]

Such a great picnic spot with children and mind relaxing jogging trails.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMg_NZ675GRRHcqLBaMeyjOOsYi-AUxrsz1-8Uk&fid=0x0:0xe654f06c80c38894"],"When":"2024-7-26"},{"Name":"Amy Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvtm7hBqZHDYxXgP_oxkelx2FGhwfW-EuwTv9rdyjxo-_-_8Nq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Huge park that’s great for families and going kayaking or paddle boarding. It has a nice kids’ water park and the public washrooms are clean. It lacks shaded areas and needs more parking!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhiI6LZ94pnToYVpCOBM3e65iW2XDRjjOoEWaE&fid=0x0:0xe654f06c80c38894"],"When":"2024-8-5"},{"Name":"Ahsaan Rizvi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVs2v-63PhGkwL4KAVyaXYhU-lYSiC0m4y-b-I-LmqV4c_0Pmnr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Rocky Point Park in Port Moody, BC, is a delightful waterfront destination offering a variety of activities for all ages. The park features a scenic boardwalk with breathtaking views of Burrard Inlet, perfect for leisurely strolls. Families can enjoy the large playground, splash pad, and picnic areas, while fitness enthusiasts take advantage of the cycling and walking trails. The park is also home to a pier for fishing and boating, adding to its recreational appeal. On-site amenities include a skate park and an outdoor pool, enhancing its appeal for youth. Rocky Point's seasonal events and festivals create a vibrant community atmosphere. With ample parking and nearby eateries, it’s a convenient and enjoyable spot for a day out. Overall, Rocky Point Park is a versatile and vibrant destination for relaxation and recreation.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3Sk3tp3LG7WznI8Cf2tN4HIdmP5fz0BEvdUt-&fid=0x0:0xe654f06c80c38894"],"When":"2024-6-21"},{"Name":"Daniel Silver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJawI80c4qwvuA-pWmht_nhIypwFKNS8vUDHnZIepoqs0gJvft7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A really nice park with lots to offer. There were a bunch of shady areas, a playground, a spray park, and a trail. Rocky Point Park is a great location to check out with kids, especially the spray park.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMHDTrTU1duTOQHATqYGqJPWdTvY5tbWA1OEIwQ&fid=0x0:0xe654f06c80c38894"],"When":"2024-8-19"},{"Name":"wah chi yip","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKKBykHMUbkrtJ4cwRRXsjOnAzAcOzwrpq-XVjovUt6A3trFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A great park all year round but summer is the best. The breathtaking views of Burrard Inlet.
There were a long broad walk along the shore.  But I didn't go to a walk for a long time.  It's a good broad walk.
A big water park and a pool in summer. It's good for whole family spending a day there. A big long picnic shelter is at the park.
We go to the Golden Spike Days on Canada Day.  It's a really nice day for the summer concerts.  Happy see a lots of people enjoying the day with family and friends.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1oVa-lqvcUlLJYY8kAR8_wmyinU4Z32oA5Lx1&fid=0x0:0xe654f06c80c38894"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Kateryna Konova","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKXpZ9gT59r8N5Phg4dth6giQHB5KWWU7de2wMWT2rICTrc-w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Rocky Point Park is a fantastic spot for a day out! With beautiful views of the water, scenic walking trails, and plenty of open space, it’s perfect for all ages. There are picnic areas, a playground, and even a splash pad for kids. The pier offers a lovely view of Burrard Inlet, and you can often spot people kayaking or paddleboarding. There are also some great food options nearby, including ice cream and seafood. Highly recommended for a relaxing day in nature!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9NmXmfBtNavUi8nXnrcvzoUwUfDqtyklLFyAL&fid=0x0:0xe654f06c80c38894"],"When":"2024-11-3"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Nicky Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWdbrHfH4GFsTTqgK1b8FKEyHjbYNyqA15i6JBcGlTzjesmGsA3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Doppio Zero Pizza truly lives up to its name when it comes to their pizza! The crust was perfectly thin and crispy, with just the right amount of chew, and the toppings were fresh, flavorful, and generously portioned.

As for the pasta, it was just okay. While it wasn’t bad by any means, it didn’t quite stand out the way their pizza did. It could use a little more flair to match the high standard set by their pizzas. I also didn’t like how the pasta noodle was too over done? 😬

The tiramisu was delicious as well.

One thing to have in mind as well is the parking.. if you go during a busy time.. you might need to park in the residential area up the street and walk..

Overall, Doppio Zero Pizza is a must-visit if you’re craving top-tier pizza. I’ll definitely be back for another round of their incredible pies!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWz1qkXa_dRoPp1tDige938yd0NVrn7CaniteR&fid=0x0:0xd23db9fd5273683e"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Youngsoo Song","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9KF6xNrz8Ca-06zFTT1f92qb4UuXywvQbI5TeswgCgRYyBqNnHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food was good and the server was friendly. I had the pizza and the burrata-- both were good and reasonably priced. I gave the food 4 because while the taste was good, the dough near the center of the pizza was so thin, the toppings kind of tore through it. Perhaps my toppings had too much moisture(?) but either way, I wish the middle had not torn.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4lvZij57sk_m_zZG-bu8SmTU-NubQmz8Gv00S&fid=0x0:0xd23db9fd5273683e"],"When":"2024-12-13"},{"Name":"Cheestravels (Cheestravels)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUu90KHK59eES_iLdA-5e4hTpzDDtNybwcTzvnfRLjdEkfHdQ5Xbw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"A tad overpriced for what they give you. Pizza is great and gnocchi is amazing. Tried a few dishes and pasta was decent but not incredible for price. Desserts were underwhelming with canned whipped cream on the sides. Was disappointed that they charge an automatic 20% gratuity charge for groups or 8 or more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVfMFJNbu9g2OV8HWFRcI2fA01-Ha4oSxuV8kV&fid=0x0:0xd23db9fd5273683e"],"When":"2024-7-27"},{"Name":"Conor Finding Realtor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWt3-qD1dIuKKhCigfciL6_hrPkCXppeVegMsaV8xEZkwNnNrs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hands down best Pizza in tri-cities. Love this place and such great Atmosphere!

I ordered the Margarita and this pizza was made to perfection. The staff had such a welcoming vibe as soon as I came through the door.

I met the owners Giulia and Daniel who are outstanding people that clearly have put there all into this restaurant. There story moving here from Italy is the icing on the cake.

If you want truly authentic Italian food come to Doppio Zero!

Thank you so much for the great service and amazing food!

I will be coming here a lot more!

Conor Finding","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNECU47lUiUaAQU5C8wuyEQ1na0QMa0t_F1iu5J&fid=0x0:0xd23db9fd5273683e"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Swimming Lion","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIoNuKoBPU8hDsJrOBlEDRPQawlWHi3C9rUvrLYtz7paaZM0w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this place !
Stone oven pizza so delicious the crust is thin, chewy and crispy
Love the carbonara  too the pork is very special hefty meat taste , fatty but not too fatty
Coffee was creamy and rich with dreamy aroma
affogato - rich and robust flavor with a pronounced coffee taste.
Servers are very friendly and attentive
Free parking lot
We went on Sunday evening around 8 pm the parking lot was pretty empty
We have party of 13 and when we pay server told us we don’t need to tip extra as for party over 8 they will automatically add 20% on top for gratuities","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOLr6M3r84e3yCErwyvFutgs65ZD7_DzQAmlugN&fid=0x0:0xd23db9fd5273683e"],"When":"2024-8-5"},{"Name":"NôMāR Åltïçłöś","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKVyqW_kOlfqb-yGJ_Ks--LFkl55GXHpZ6S3YNX2dqaycCck_x=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice, quaint Italian restaurant at Como Lake Ave., in Coquitlam. Open kitchen well depicts their cleanness and pizza craftsmanship.This is my new go-to.🍕","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzpZBxs-lPZeno12i-7kpMiuuoOoeBWV2WbyXP&fid=0x0:0xd23db9fd5273683e"],"When":"2024-8-18"},{"Name":"Joshua Fang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVYKjZadI3GLvYlhP8JzW1RAWYF0hYt7IB342AdEQBC7hNDQVNQg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pretty crazy that this spot is in Coquitlam. [{"Name":"Sanjana Ranthilini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX6POSb5GYlpUu6r8OK46uloIQlaxX1HTFGthMRpYIbdb6TmfXa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was great and the prices were really worth it. The servers were also super friendly and engaged. I loved their Biriyani.  It had so many flavors and spices; probably the best Indian Biryani I've ever tried in Canada.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXTGY7-2nmj9Ngp5kyTGTs1U-WVcepCC8OBSuI&fid=0x0:0x587a7dd9814b3e2e"],"When":"2024-8-7"},{"Name":"Sathiyaseelan Suhashini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGCDhZwAvUF3Q8iMEpEx8TQCvKbwiXzYFJN0uOrenEt7v0wxGX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A gem found in Coquitlam Centre, walking distance from sky train station.

Great taste and portions are reasonable for the price. They have great variety and mix of many dishes.

We tried Chicken Samosa, Lamp Tikka Masala, Garlic Naan, Onion Kulcha and Paratha.

They take a while to bring food, but I found it fresh and good in taste that is worth the time.

Customer service is attentive and good.

It would be around $20 without desserts and appetizers.

I found their dessert portion to be extremely unreasonable as it is way too small for $6.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNogZYG0qiPCt0JxZqa14zAKS2qGw2MpO4HCwZ3&fid=0x0:0x587a7dd9814b3e2e"],"When":"2024-8-8"},{"Name":"Nicky Choi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWdbrHfH4GFsTTqgK1b8FKEyHjbYNyqA15i6JBcGlTzjesmGsA3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I must admit this place is pretty darn good! I haven’t had much Indian food in a restaurant t but this butter chicken curry was bang on! I got mine a little spicier and I loved it! The Samosa on the other hand was a little too salty for my liking, but it might differ for other people. Next time I’m wanting to try the vegetarian Samosa, hoping it has a lot of potatoes in it to even out the saltiness. 😅 all in all the server was really really polite and helpful and they came around several times asking if the food was good.They were trying to help us all the time and I appreciate it the quick response to all our requests. It got pretty busy during the evening but it’s definitely a place you should come on by if you’re in town.

Price: average - $16.99 for butter chicken curry doesn’t include naan or rice. Naan on the side is $2.99 + get  each person would be about $25 at least for dinner to be safe’","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNdI80T2Z7E1UZFnnPyr_bKYqpKzm18Ain0HVgU&fid=0x0:0x587a7dd9814b3e2e"],"When":"2024-1-29"},{"Name":"Jimmy Marse","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ6EabICLG0QSjGi0nBueVj96UcPn2rgpvZ0QCseNTv0rxJuA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was taken here the first time by my East Indian coworker and I started falling in love with this restaurant.  Then I brought my wife a week after, then my daughter 2 weeks after that.  The food was very delicious.  The service was so decent and comfortable that made me feel like eating at home.  Shout out to Simmer who has provided us the top notch service and we will definitely visit again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTJAeyDX4zO9K5P9JaHHOWVKyTDUt-u18m0pl4&fid=0x0:0x587a7dd9814b3e2e"],"When":"2023-11-2"},{"Name":"marrina e","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXnp2QqU2IP2AgIC84yOheubXxBGmiXzONKBJBU40ZTC7pN3Qme=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food, great prices!  Gagan was an amazing server. Ordered more but forgot to take photos","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYVskaQhrORYoMOQzdd5lkIZ1JKICT5jxJ6Vx2&fid=0x0:0x587a7dd9814b3e2e"],"When":"2024-10-19"},{"Name":"Hashan Peiris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQS5tXYmTSP8F6gc8CzViRW9uUkD3rHwc2GCIQJ7tX0r6Ne1oo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went there with my friends. The time taken to serve food was good as every one ordered different dishes. Their food was worth to share with someone. Specially the grill platter was delicious and the portion was large. Their naan and roti were fresh. The chai was refreshing. The staff was friendly and tried to make us comfort during the stay.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM3zu_pVMlPLhWlG7SWdPP3anp_GM5bae5_YduH&fid=0x0:0x587a7dd9814b3e2e"],"When":"2023-12-25"},{"Name":"Attila Szamoskozi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2AAt3w8V6vnjRCqXfUE0xqvAqQuLl4Zs8C3rG6vUvIyME7FzU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had the lunch special curry chicken.  Very well executed.  The sauce on the chicken was very flavorful and spicy.  I ordered it hot, and it was definitely hot!  Chickpeas were great also.  Slightly different sauce on the chickpeas.  I felt like the rice could have used a bit more seasoning on it's own but paired with the curry sauce it was great.  Very friendly service.  Would definitely return!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN9-I7nRRrsiNtkPhy1aYk9MoeUxt1aEZXSE8kA&fid=0x0:0x587a7dd9814b3e2e"],"When":"2023-8-11"},{"Name":"Harpalsinh Zala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-TYmhNmmiMJilxaSem0j6A44icna87829D8HIiQB6FuO_IPp4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing vegetarian food! The flavors were authentic, fresh, and perfectly spiced. Great ambiance and friendly staff. Highly recommend Lazzez's Grill for a delicious Indian dining experience!","Images":null,"When":""}]
